WEBVTT

00:01.702 --> 00:04.604
<i>[ Swing ]</i>

00:16.000 --> 00:22.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:18.446 --> 01:20.346
[ Woman In Car]
Why in God's name...

01:20.448 --> 01:22.507
would the Stantons
have their summer house...

01:22.617 --> 01:24.482
out in the middle
of all this yuck?

01:24.586 --> 01:26.486
[ Man ]
I don't think they do.

01:26.588 --> 01:28.488
What's that supposed to mean?

01:28.590 --> 01:30.490
It means we're lost.

01:30.592 --> 01:33.493
We're just gonna keep driving
until we hit someone's pig?

01:33.595 --> 01:36.120
- Binky.
- How in God's name
could you drag me down here...

01:36.231 --> 01:38.631
to Yuckville, West Virginia,
when I'm 40 months pregnant?

01:38.733 --> 01:40.724
<i>Not that that was my idea.</i>

01:40.835 --> 01:42.996
Don't start that again.
You agreed.

01:43.137 --> 01:45.264
Against my better judgement.

01:45.406 --> 01:48.136
Well, you will have
your own personal beach
house to console you.

01:48.243 --> 01:49.801
[ Sighs ]

01:49.944 --> 01:53.311
Most husbands
find it unnecessary to bribe
their wives to reproduce.

01:53.414 --> 01:56.281
[ Chuckles ]
That's why I "dwuv doo."

01:56.384 --> 01:59.945
Oh! God, haven't these people
ever heard of pavement?

02:00.054 --> 02:03.581
Oh, Huntsy.
Something happened.

02:03.691 --> 02:06.251
What? What is it?

02:06.361 --> 02:09.626
[ Groaning, Squealing ]

02:09.731 --> 02:12.199
I think the kid wants out
at the next stop.

02:17.939 --> 02:20.737
My wife is having a baby.
Where's the nearest hospital?

02:20.842 --> 02:22.742
<i>[ Chickens Clucking ]</i>

02:22.844 --> 02:26.143
You might try
down in Jane Lew.

02:26.247 --> 02:28.943
- [ Groaning ]
- How close are we?

02:29.083 --> 02:33.383
Oh...I'd say about...

02:35.723 --> 02:38.658
<i>forty, forty-five miles.</i>

02:38.760 --> 02:41.888
- Is he crazy?
- There's no time!

02:43.164 --> 02:45.394
Well...

02:45.500 --> 02:48.230
the Hollowmade Hospital's
in Jupiter Hollow.

02:48.336 --> 02:50.270
It's about three miles, but--

02:50.371 --> 02:52.396
Hollowmade!
Thank you!

02:52.540 --> 02:54.974
[ Binky ] How did you ever get me
out of Park Avenue?

02:55.076 --> 02:57.476
You ain't gonna get in there.

02:59.113 --> 03:01.104
Garth?

03:02.350 --> 03:04.318
It's time again.

03:04.419 --> 03:07.320
<i>[ Swing Continues ]</i>

03:07.422 --> 03:17.320
<i>.</i>

03:23.871 --> 03:26.305
<i>[ Toilet Flushing ]</i>

03:26.407 --> 03:29.843
<i>[ Woman Humming ]</i>

03:29.978 --> 03:32.674
Where do you want me
to put this, doc?

03:32.780 --> 03:35.647
Just put it right here,
Eufus, on your way out.

03:35.750 --> 03:38.719
Check with me tomorrow,
and don't worry about it.

03:38.820 --> 03:41.812
<i>. [ Both Humming ]</i>

03:41.923 --> 03:43.823
<i>[ Bell Jingles ]</i>

03:43.925 --> 03:46.155
Mmm, that's good cider,
Nanny Lewis.

03:46.260 --> 03:48.820
Uh, could you take that
down to the lab?

03:48.930 --> 03:51.922
<i>. [ Humming Continues ]</i>

03:55.203 --> 03:57.933
Snack time!

03:59.574 --> 04:02.873
<i>- [ Horn Honks ]
-[ Hunt ] There's the hospital, Harlan.</i>

04:02.977 --> 04:06.105
[ Tires Screeching ]

04:06.214 --> 04:08.774
- Cross your legs.
- Hunt!

04:08.916 --> 04:12.477
Tell them I want my own room.

04:12.587 --> 04:15.215
[ Bell Jingles ]

04:15.323 --> 04:17.450
My wife is having a baby.

04:17.558 --> 04:21.584
Oh, well!
Jane Lew Hospital's probably
what you're lookin' for.

04:21.696 --> 04:23.960
- This is a hospital?
- Oh, yes.

04:24.065 --> 04:26.533
But it's for employees
of Hollowmade only.

04:26.634 --> 04:28.829
- Company policy.
- This is an emergency.

04:28.970 --> 04:33.373
Oh, I'd love to help you out,
but I can't do anything without
Mr. Stokes' authorization.

04:33.474 --> 04:35.442
- He's a real stickler--
- Mr. Stokes?

04:35.576 --> 04:37.601
He owns the Hollowmade factory.

04:37.745 --> 04:40.578
Lives in the big, gray
house, right over there.

04:41.649 --> 04:44.174
[ Nanny ] That's gratitude!

04:44.285 --> 04:46.185
I shan't be a minute.

04:46.287 --> 04:48.983
Hunt, where are you going?

04:49.090 --> 04:50.990
Hunt? Hunt!

04:54.562 --> 04:56.792
You all right
back there, Iona?

04:56.898 --> 04:59.298
Don't you fret.
I'm just fine.

05:00.401 --> 05:02.426
- Howdy, Iona.
- Mornin', Jake.

05:03.905 --> 05:06.237
- Mr. Stokes!
- Doctor...

05:06.340 --> 05:08.535
I'd like you to meet
Mr. and Mrs. Shelton.

05:08.643 --> 05:10.941
They're the new owners
of Hollowmade Furniture.

05:11.045 --> 05:13.843
Ooh, scrub up, Doc.
Your new boss is having a baby!

05:13.948 --> 05:15.848
[ Stammering ]

05:15.917 --> 05:19.114
<i>[ Binky ] Oh, look at this place.
What a dump!</i>

05:19.220 --> 05:21.211
<i>[ Garth Knocks At Door ]
Hi, Doc.</i>

05:21.322 --> 05:25.190
- Guess what?
- [ Exhales ]

05:27.295 --> 05:29.195
Ohhh.

05:33.101 --> 05:35.626
<i>[ Gasps ] I hate needles!</i>

05:35.770 --> 05:38.432
Now, hold on a second.
It'll just be a little prick.

05:38.573 --> 05:42.407
Yeah, that's what got me
into this mess.

05:47.815 --> 05:52.013
[ Grunting, Squealing ]

05:53.688 --> 05:55.679
It-It's a girl.

05:57.592 --> 05:59.685
Coming, Iona.

05:59.794 --> 06:03.423
[ Baby Crying ]

06:03.531 --> 06:05.522
There you are.

06:05.633 --> 06:09.433
[ Crying Continues ]

06:09.570 --> 06:12.539
<i>[ Panting, Groaning ]</i>

06:12.673 --> 06:17.474
I like that lamp.
That new since last time?

06:17.578 --> 06:21.344
Yeah. One more push.

06:21.449 --> 06:24.145
<i>[ Moaning ]</i>

06:24.252 --> 06:26.152
It's a girl.

06:26.254 --> 06:28.154
[ Baby Crying ]

06:31.292 --> 06:33.658
[ Panting, Grunts ]

06:34.996 --> 06:38.295
[ Gasps ]
It's another girl!

06:38.399 --> 06:41.960
<i>[ Binky ] Doctor! There's
something stuck in here!</i>

06:42.103 --> 06:45.561
<i>[ Doctor ] Nanny, I think you'd
better get in here quick.</i>

06:45.706 --> 06:48.641
[ Baby Crying ]

06:48.743 --> 06:50.836
<i>[ Binky Screams ]</i>

06:50.945 --> 06:53.209
<i>[ Doctor ] Nanny!</i>

06:53.314 --> 06:56.112
[ Crying Continues ]

07:04.625 --> 07:07.321
[ Gasps ] It's another girl!

07:07.428 --> 07:10.022
[ Baby Crying ]

07:17.438 --> 07:19.736
Well, I hope you both
wanted twins...

07:19.841 --> 07:21.968
<i>'cause that's
what you both got.</i>

07:22.109 --> 07:24.009
<i>Girls!</i>

07:24.111 --> 07:26.136
- Wonderful!
- Damn.

07:26.247 --> 07:28.408
That was the messiest,
ickiest...

07:28.516 --> 07:31.883
most unbearably primitive
experience I've ever had.

07:31.986 --> 07:34.955
Ohhh. If it's
all right with you...

07:35.056 --> 07:38.389
I-I'd like to name them
after my great aunts.

07:38.492 --> 07:40.392
I shudder to ask.

07:40.494 --> 07:43.292
- Rose and Sadie.
- Ugh.

07:43.397 --> 07:46.366
You'll look so lovely
in that tiara.

07:46.467 --> 07:48.458
Tsk. All right.

07:48.569 --> 07:51.129
We'll name them
Rose and Sadie.

07:51.272 --> 07:54.673
- What color are the stones?
- [ Scoffs ]

07:54.775 --> 07:57.505
<i>[ Footsteps ]</i>

08:05.519 --> 08:07.453
You done real good.

08:07.555 --> 08:09.819
[ Sighs ]

08:09.924 --> 08:12.358
Oh, Garth!

08:14.729 --> 08:18.324
Why, that's
your "purtiest" one.

08:18.432 --> 08:21.196
[ Sighs ]

08:21.302 --> 08:24.794
Well, what
should we call them?

08:26.841 --> 08:29.275
It's just a duck.

08:29.410 --> 08:31.935
<i>Oh,you mean, the, uh--</i>

08:35.082 --> 08:37.107
How about Rose and Sadie?

08:37.217 --> 08:39.914
That's "purty"!

08:40.020 --> 08:43.183
<i>- [ Babies Fussing ]
-Sadie and Rose.</i>

09:21.395 --> 09:23.295
<i>[ Woman ]
Good morning, Moramax.</i>

09:23.397 --> 09:25.627
<i>-[ Man ] Good morning. Hi, there.
- Thanks very much.</i>

09:25.733 --> 09:28.201
<i>-[ Phones Ringing ]
- Thank you. Miss Davis isn't in yet.</i>

09:28.302 --> 09:31.100
Would you take a seat
in the reception area?

09:31.238 --> 09:34.105
<i>- [ Chattering ]
- [ Intercom Buzzes ]</i>

09:34.208 --> 09:36.836
<i>- Yes?
-[ Man On Intercom ]
She's coming.</i>

09:36.944 --> 09:40.573
- It's Sadie!
- [ Employees Gasping ]

09:40.681 --> 09:42.672
<i>[ Woman ] Good morning,
Moramax. Please hold.</i>

09:42.783 --> 09:45.217
<i>Good morning, Moramax.
Please hold.</i>

09:45.319 --> 09:47.787
<i>Good morning, Moramax.</i>

09:50.925 --> 09:53.758
<i>[ Quiet Chattering,
Phones Ringing ]</i>

09:53.861 --> 09:57.763
<i>- Good morning, Miss Shel--
- Depreciation schedule,
on my desk by 5:00.</i>

09:57.865 --> 10:02.768
<i>Stuart. You know, when I ask
for demographics, I expect you
to include all age groups.</i>

10:02.903 --> 10:06.270
- Uh, children 7 to 1 3 don't
purchase stock, Ms. Shelton.
- I did.

10:06.374 --> 10:08.774
<i>- Miss Shelton, the--
- Is this how we dress
for the office?</i>

10:08.876 --> 10:11.310
- You look like a blood clot.
- Everything's ready
for the board meeting.

10:11.412 --> 10:13.312
Flow charts.

10:13.414 --> 10:17.646
- Profit pyramid.
- I hope you'll be pleased.
We were here until--

10:17.752 --> 10:21.085
What's going on in research?
More money for more lab rats?

10:21.188 --> 10:24.453
Uh, some of our new products seem
to create, um, adverse reactions.

10:24.558 --> 10:26.753
Get tougher rats.

10:28.195 --> 10:30.629
<i>- Where's my sister?
- Not in yet.</i>

10:30.731 --> 10:34.360
- Dieting again, are we?
- Shhh. Not here.

10:34.468 --> 10:36.368
[ Clears Throat ]

10:36.504 --> 10:39.496
- [ Elevator Bell Dings ]
- Good morning,Judy.
Come on, Duke.

10:39.640 --> 10:42.575
- Oh, hi, Rose.
- I know I'm late. It's just,
I got to walking in the park...

10:42.676 --> 10:46.772
and it was so beautiful, and I,
I found this cute little guy
and he was lost.

10:46.881 --> 10:49.509
- Rose.
- And I think I'm gonna
call him Duke.

10:49.617 --> 10:52.518
- Because I've always wanted
to have a dog named Duke!
- Let go, Rose.

10:52.620 --> 10:55.180
- Oh, God! Duke!
Oh, what have I done?
- Push the button.

10:55.289 --> 10:58.019
<i>- Oh, call someone.
Do something. Duke.
- The down button, Rose.</i>

10:58.125 --> 11:00.719
<i>- Oh, help me!
Call the security!
- It'll be all right.</i>

11:00.828 --> 11:03.456
<i>- Duke!
- See? There he is.</i>

11:03.564 --> 11:05.862
Oh, Duke, you're okay.
I'm so sorry.

11:05.966 --> 11:08.457
- I didn't mean to do it.
- [ Snarls, Barks ]

11:08.569 --> 11:11.538
- It's all right. I deserve it.
- [ Barking ]

11:11.639 --> 11:14.540
Rose, why don't I take Duke
while you're in the meeting?

11:14.642 --> 11:17.475
Oh, the meeting.
Oh, I almost forgot.

11:17.578 --> 11:20.604
I--I'm just not myself today.
[ Panting ]

11:20.714 --> 11:23.182
Or any other day.

11:27.555 --> 11:29.750
You're late. The meeting's
in two minutes.

11:29.857 --> 11:32.121
I know, but, Sadie,
do I have to go?

11:32.226 --> 11:35.718
I sit there, and everyone
looks at me like I--like I'm--
because--especially today.

11:35.830 --> 11:38.958
<i>I'm just not grounded.
I'm not centered in the way
I should be, because last night...</i>

11:39.066 --> 11:41.432
Dr.Jay and I,
we were having this--

11:41.535 --> 11:44.368
this candlelight dinner
and, you know, too much wine.

11:44.505 --> 11:47.838
<i>I started opening up,
and he started closing up
like he usually does.</i>

11:47.942 --> 11:50.877
But I started talking about
getting married and having kids...

11:50.978 --> 11:53.572
and maybe a goat
and some ducks...

11:53.681 --> 11:55.842
and a little garden
with fresh veggies.

11:55.950 --> 11:59.113
<i>- You know how I love to chop and--
- What happened?</i>

11:59.220 --> 12:02.485
- Oh, we broke up.
- Good riddance.

12:02.590 --> 12:05.252
- [ Sobbing ]
- You are so completely out of sync.

12:05.359 --> 12:08.760
You're dreaming about
growing old in the country
while other women your age--

12:08.863 --> 12:10.956
<i>- Our age.
- Don't interrupt!</i>

12:11.065 --> 12:15.434
Are thinking about tummy tucks.
I tell you, it's not normal.
Now, stop it. Stop it.

12:15.536 --> 12:17.970
Do you want one of the board
members to see you?

12:18.072 --> 12:20.768
They'll say you're
a sniveling, hysterical,
pre-periodic twit!

12:20.908 --> 12:23.934
I have a right
to my own feelings, Sadie,
and I am not a twit.

12:24.078 --> 12:26.808
I may be pre-periodic,
and I may be hysterical. So what?

12:26.914 --> 12:29.314
So there are drugs for those things,
and we make most of them.

12:29.383 --> 12:31.613
I could just kick myself
when I act this way.

12:31.719 --> 12:34.449
Splash some water
on your face and maintain.

12:34.555 --> 12:37.388
- Oh, Rose!
- [ Woman On Intercom ]
Dr.Jay for Rose.

12:37.491 --> 12:39.721
Put him on. Look,Jay--

12:39.827 --> 12:42.694
- Rose, Rose,
I'm so glad I reached you.
- I'm not--

12:42.796 --> 12:46.254
I'm sorry, honey.
It's not that I haven't thought
of the--the "M" word.

12:46.367 --> 12:49.894
[ Chuckles ] I have. I have.
No, I maybe, uh, might.

12:50.037 --> 12:52.471
It's just--
You know what it is?

12:52.606 --> 12:56.064
Well, I'll be honest with you.
It's your goddamned family!

12:56.210 --> 12:59.407
The idea of your blood-sucking
sister Sadie...

12:59.513 --> 13:01.947
as a permanent
fixture in my life...

13:02.016 --> 13:04.314
is so inexpressibly nauseating--

13:04.418 --> 13:07.819
- Well, take a purge.
- [ Dial Tone ]

13:07.922 --> 13:12.188
I'm just gonna throw myself
into your work. Who was that?

13:12.293 --> 13:14.488
A heavy breather
with intestinal woe.

13:14.595 --> 13:17.962
- Oh, dear. Paw prints.
- Look, I'm fed up with you.

13:18.065 --> 13:19.965
You're a senior vice president...

13:20.067 --> 13:23.002
and the window washer knows more
about this company than you do.

13:23.137 --> 13:26.197
You're so wispy, wispy, wispy.
Why can't you focus?

13:26.340 --> 13:28.900
- I'm going to.
- And these weird attacks
of domesticity.

13:29.043 --> 13:31.102
- Where do they come from?
- I don't know.

13:31.245 --> 13:34.339
You're going to have to see
Dr. Sullivan, I insist.
As soon as possible.

13:34.448 --> 13:38.282
- He didn't stop you
from getting married.
- That was a brief fiasco.

13:38.385 --> 13:41.877
Well, this fiasco would like
to have a few words with you.

13:41.989 --> 13:43.980
- I tried to tell him.
- Hi, Michael.

13:44.091 --> 13:46.321
What are you doing here?
I'm going into a board meeting.

13:46.427 --> 13:48.622
Well, that's certainly
more important than your son.

13:48.729 --> 13:50.856
- [ Gun Noises ]
- Yo, Ma. It's me, Sly.

13:50.965 --> 13:55.299
It's your day with him.
You're not dumping him on me
five minutes before a meeting.

13:55.402 --> 13:58.235
I am not dumping him on you.
I just want to know
the meaning of this.

13:58.372 --> 14:01.034
- He said
you gave it to him.
- I did.

14:01.175 --> 14:04.008
- Do you mind telling me why?
- He earned it.

14:04.111 --> 14:06.011
How?

14:06.113 --> 14:08.673
A hundred dollars
for every "C," two hundred
dollars for every "B"--

14:08.749 --> 14:12.276
You pay our child to learn?

14:12.386 --> 14:15.753
Why not?
Let's just call it a, a perk.

14:15.856 --> 14:20.520
You're out of your mind!
You're raising a child,
not a, not a C.E.O.

14:20.628 --> 14:22.687
Well, perhaps I'll raise both.

14:22.796 --> 14:26.823
<i>- [ Boy Laughing ]
- Oh, I got you. I got you.</i>

14:26.934 --> 14:29.164
Oh, all right.
I'll take the money back...

14:29.303 --> 14:31.771
if you'll just...
get him out of here.

14:31.905 --> 14:34.567
Hey, that's my money!
Mine!

14:34.708 --> 14:37.074
Spoken like a true Shelton.

14:38.479 --> 14:41.209
<i>-Jason!
- [ Yelling, Laughing ]</i>

14:41.315 --> 14:43.374
Come along, Rose.

14:43.484 --> 14:46.476
[ Panting ] I-I don't even know
what's on the agenda.

14:46.587 --> 14:49.385
There's a ridiculous little
company we've had forever.

14:49.490 --> 14:52.618
- I'm going to ask the board
to off-load it.
- What's it called?

14:52.726 --> 14:55.354
Hollowmade.

14:55.462 --> 14:59.057
[ Distant Chattering ]

14:59.166 --> 15:01.361
<i>.</i>

15:01.468 --> 15:05.404
Let's hear it for
the Hollowmade shop class
and marching band!

15:05.506 --> 15:07.633
<i>- [ Cheering ]
- Playing, well, frankly...</i>

15:07.775 --> 15:09.675
I didn't recognize
the tune, but--

15:09.777 --> 15:12.211
[ Laughing ]

15:12.313 --> 15:14.406
Now, to head up this fight...

15:14.515 --> 15:18.349
we think we got somebody who's
more than a match for Moramax.

15:18.452 --> 15:20.920
<i>- [ Booing ]
- Hollowmade's
own factory foreman...</i>

15:21.021 --> 15:25.788
Miss Guts and Gumption,
Miss No-Nonsense herself,
Rose Ratliff!.

15:25.893 --> 15:29.590
<i>- Come on up here, girl!
- Yee-ha!</i>

15:29.697 --> 15:32.427
<i>-[ Cheering, Whistling ]
- Come on, you spry chicken.</i>

15:32.533 --> 15:34.831
- Go get 'em, Rose!
- Think big, Rosie!

15:34.935 --> 15:39.235
<i>Thank you. Whoo!</i>

15:39.373 --> 15:43.173
- [ Chuckles ]
- I appreciate that, Mayor.
I really do.

15:43.277 --> 15:46.212
I don't know about you all,
but I'm mad as a wet wasp.

15:46.347 --> 15:50.113
<i>-[ Drum Rim Shot ]
- I've been doing some checking up
on these Moramax folks.</i>

15:50.217 --> 15:54.813
Last year, they put
300 Santa Clauses out of work,
and right before Christmas too.

15:54.922 --> 15:57.686
<i>-[ Crowd Murmuring ]
- And now, it's Hollowmade
they want.</i>

15:57.791 --> 16:01.750
- [ Booing,Jeering ]
- No tellin' what they got
up their designer sleeves.

16:01.862 --> 16:04.387
Could be condos,
a ski resort.

16:04.498 --> 16:07.365
Strip-mining's one
sure thing comes to mind.

16:07.468 --> 16:11.404
Are we gonna let 'em swoop down
on us like a bunch of turkey
buzzards in business suits?

16:11.538 --> 16:14.439
- [ Together] No!
- Pick our bones clean?

16:14.541 --> 16:17.942
- Take our factory,
our jobs, our way of life?
- [ Together] No!

16:18.045 --> 16:20.605
Can we outsnake 'em?
Hell, yeah!

16:20.714 --> 16:23.649
[ All Hissing ]

16:23.751 --> 16:27.312
Now, go on and get out there
and buy those canned peaches
and ceramic items.

16:27.421 --> 16:30.584
Mayor Finkar brought his
two-headed calf all the way
up from Jane Lew.

16:30.691 --> 16:33.421
And it's a beauty. Whoo!
Twenty-five cents a look.

16:33.527 --> 16:36.291
- [ Laughing ]
- Come on, we got
to raise some money...

16:36.397 --> 16:40.163
so I can go up north
and raise some hell and kick
some snooty New York ass.

16:40.267 --> 16:43.759
- [ Cheering ]
- [ Drum Rim Shot ]

16:43.904 --> 16:46.702
- Are you with me?
- [ Together] Yeah!

16:46.807 --> 16:49.970
'Cause right here, right now,
we've got the Swamp Mud Boys...

16:50.077 --> 16:52.978
featurin' my sweet sister,
Miss Sadie Ratliff.

16:53.080 --> 16:56.481
<i>- Hit it!
- .. [ Polka ]</i>

16:56.617 --> 17:01.077
<i>.</i>

17:01.188 --> 17:04.646
. Well, hello,Jupiter Hollow
I know you're doin' fine .

17:04.758 --> 17:08.421
. Every day you work the factory
Every night, a jug of wine .

17:08.529 --> 17:10.429
. But now them bums
at Moramax .

17:10.531 --> 17:12.431
. They're tryin'
to milk us dry.

17:12.532 --> 17:15.194
. But you all knows my sister Rose
will sound the battle cry.

17:15.301 --> 17:16.859
Yee-ha!

17:17.003 --> 17:20.804
. Sister Rose
is gonna kick 'em in their
little-lo-lay-hee-hoo .

17:20.907 --> 17:23.569
<i> Their little-lo-lay-hee-hoo
Their little-lo-lay-hee-hoo.</i>

17:23.676 --> 17:27.579
. Every cent's
gonna help us kick their
little-lo-lay-hee-hoo .

17:27.714 --> 17:31.480
. Hi-dee-olay-hee
Little-lo-lay-hee-hoo .

17:31.585 --> 17:33.985
<i>-.[ Yodeling Continues ]
- Ha-ha-ha!</i>

17:37.958 --> 17:40.620
[ Mooing ]

17:50.170 --> 17:52.138
<i>[ Cow Mooing,
Crowd Cheering ]</i>

17:52.272 --> 17:54.797
<i>[ Sadie Shelton ]
The most fiscally prudent action
at this point...</i>

17:54.942 --> 17:57.001
<i>is to divest ourselves
of Hollowmade.</i>

17:57.144 --> 17:59.374
It's a little backwoods
furniture factory.

17:59.480 --> 18:01.812
They actually still make
porch rockers.

18:01.915 --> 18:05.078
<i>Now, the opportunities
for expansion are virtually nil...</i>

18:05.185 --> 18:08.211
and the buyer has offered us
a most attractive price.

18:08.322 --> 18:11.416
So you can see, gentlemen, that
were we to liquidate Hollowmade...

18:11.525 --> 18:15.291
the return on our investment
would in fact be quadrupled.

18:15.395 --> 18:18.990
<i>- [ Men Murmuring ]
- Oh, but liquidate--</i>

18:19.099 --> 18:22.762
<i>I mean, aren't there
other considerations?
Uh, may I make a point?</i>

18:22.903 --> 18:25.804
I'm sitting listening here,
and I--what I--

18:25.906 --> 18:29.398
I'm feeling, uh, deeply inside--

18:29.543 --> 18:31.704
I mean, what it is, is--

18:31.812 --> 18:34.781
I mean, things are just not
computing exactly right.

18:34.882 --> 18:36.747
<i>I mean--Sorry.</i>

18:36.850 --> 18:39.751
Gentlemen,
help yourself to Danish.

18:39.853 --> 18:42.253
<i>-[ Men Murmuring ]
- [ Panting ] Oh, God.</i>

18:42.356 --> 18:46.258
How many times have I told you
you're not to talk about things
you don't understand?

18:46.360 --> 18:49.261
- I know, but--
- Where do you get
this bleeding heart from?

18:49.363 --> 18:52.264
I can't help it.
I think the way Daddy bought
the company is so sweet.

18:52.366 --> 18:56.132
If Daddy were alive, he'd be
the first to agree with me.
Sweetness wouldn't stop him...

18:56.236 --> 18:59.672
from taking a huge profit
out of some toothpick mill
in Hickville, West Virginia.

18:59.806 --> 19:02.639
Now, eat the goddamn muffin.
And for God's sake,
try to show some poise.

19:02.743 --> 19:04.643
<i>- Poise.
- [ Man ] Miss Shelton?</i>

19:04.745 --> 19:06.838
<i>- [ Together] Yes?
- We're for it.</i>

19:06.947 --> 19:09.882
But we don't want
any publicity about it--

19:09.983 --> 19:14.352
<i>uh, people losing
their jobs and all that.</i>

19:14.454 --> 19:17.480
<i>From a P.R. standpoint...</i>

19:17.591 --> 19:20.754
<i>we might look rather heartless
if we shut down the mill.</i>

19:20.861 --> 19:25.264
<i>Last year's hostile takeover
of the Santa City chain
hurt us immeasurably.</i>

19:25.365 --> 19:28.562
<i>-[ Men Murmuring ]
- Oh! Everyone's
forgotten all about that.</i>

19:28.669 --> 19:31.137
I know I have.

19:31.271 --> 19:35.105
Three hundred angry Santas
picketing our world headquarters
tend to be remembered vividly.

19:35.208 --> 19:38.006
- Yes, indeed they do.
- [ Men Murmuring ]

19:38.111 --> 19:41.945
Gentlemen, gentlemen.
And Rose.

19:42.015 --> 19:44.745
<i>You have my full and complete
assurance that the buyer...</i>

19:44.851 --> 19:47.786
Mr. Fabio Alberici, will
continue running this factory...

19:47.888 --> 19:50.049
in concert
with current management.

19:50.157 --> 19:53.991
Therefore, I urge you
to give your most serious
consideration to a "yes" vote...

19:54.094 --> 19:57.757
<i>to the Hollowmade sale
initiative at next Wednesday's
stockholders' meeting.</i>

19:57.864 --> 20:00.765
So the people of Jupiter Hollow
are in support?

20:00.867 --> 20:05.167
Oh, they are!
I assure you.

20:05.606 --> 20:08.973
<i>[ Chattering, Laughter ]</i>

20:09.076 --> 20:12.910
- [ Grunting ]
- Oh! Did you see that?

20:13.013 --> 20:16.278
Oh, Sadie, you were so good.
You got 'em singin' and dancin'.

20:16.383 --> 20:19.546
- That's gonna add
plenty to the fund.
- Oh, the fund, the fund.

20:19.653 --> 20:22.713
- You sung so good, Sadie.
Didn't she, Rose?
- Oh, she did.

20:22.823 --> 20:25.451
What's wrong with you?
Don't you want to save
Jupiter Hollow?

20:25.559 --> 20:30.462
I know it's small of me, but
this doesn't strike me as a way
of life much worth preserving.

20:30.564 --> 20:33.897
- Oh!
- Hey, Sadie!
I got this thing all wrapped up.

20:34.001 --> 20:37.164
I'm gonna get that little squealer
right there just for you.

20:37.304 --> 20:40.364
- Oh, great, Petey!
- Yeah? Wanna go get
a grape soda?

20:40.507 --> 20:44.238
Not with a man
covered with pig poop.
No, sir, I don't.

20:44.344 --> 20:48.508
I'm not good enough for you?
You're gettin' a little above
your raisin', if you ask me.

20:48.615 --> 20:51.106
She's just kiddin', Petey.
That's sure the truth.

20:51.218 --> 20:53.311
You been above your raisin'
all your life.

20:53.420 --> 20:55.650
- Mighty nice job, ladies.
- We're gonna win.

20:55.756 --> 20:58.850
How can you say this is
a way of life not much
worth preservin'?

20:58.959 --> 21:02.122
Just look at this.
How can you not just
love this place?

21:02.229 --> 21:04.390
Oh, God, Rose,
I wish I knew.

21:04.498 --> 21:08.025
I, I feel like the real me is
all cooped up inside, you know?

21:08.135 --> 21:11.434
<i>And I want so many things.
I want designer clothes.</i>

21:11.571 --> 21:16.304
I want to see the world.
I want a penthouse in the sky
and a maid to pick up after me.

21:16.410 --> 21:19.573
I want to say things
like "keep the change."

21:19.680 --> 21:22.240
[ Sighs ]
God, sometimes I get so bored...

21:22.382 --> 21:25.146
I find myself just prayin'
for a U.F.O. sightin'.

21:25.252 --> 21:28.415
I'd stand here and I'd say,
"Come and get me.
Come and get me."

21:28.522 --> 21:31.582
Yeah, well, you're bored 'cause
you got no sense of purpose.

21:31.692 --> 21:34.490
Why don't you help me
with this Moramax mess?

21:34.594 --> 21:37.586
Over my dead--
What do you mean?

21:37.698 --> 21:41.134
Leave town?
Go to New York City?

21:41.234 --> 21:45.170
- It's a dangerous, dirty,
low-down place, Sadie.
- I know! I know!

21:45.272 --> 21:48.207
Oh, my God! What'll I wear?
I gotta get my hair cut.

21:48.308 --> 21:51.175
Oh! This is just
the sense of purpose I need.

21:51.278 --> 21:54.372
I gotta get me some
of those press-on nails.
Do those things stay on?

21:54.481 --> 21:58.042
I wouldn't want 'em
floppin' off in any of those
fancy nightclubs.

21:58.151 --> 22:01.314
Listen. Nightclubs?
This is business. Now,
you get a grip on yourself.

22:01.421 --> 22:04.413
We're goin' to New York City!
We're goin' to New York City!

22:04.524 --> 22:08.426
Ooh! Oh! What are you
gonna tell Roone?

22:08.528 --> 22:10.428
I don't know.

22:10.530 --> 22:13.556
Just keep your eye
on the ball.

22:13.667 --> 22:16.795
<i>[ Ducks Quacking,
Announcer:Indistinct ]</i>

22:24.277 --> 22:28.043
Yeah! Ha-ha-ha!
Hey, how's my baby?

22:28.148 --> 22:30.139
[ Both Moaning ]

22:30.250 --> 22:34.687
If I can birdie the windmill
hole this year, I got a good
chance of winnin' the Masters.

22:34.788 --> 22:37.655
- Oh, look at that!
- Whoo-hoo! You see that?

22:37.758 --> 22:41.660
- Isn't that somethin'?
- When this tournament's over, I'm
gonna take you away for a week.

22:41.762 --> 22:44.993
- I'm gonna take you up to the
tiptop of Blue Ridge Mountain.
- [ Laughs ]

22:45.098 --> 22:48.124
- It might be more like
the Empire State Building.
- What?

22:48.235 --> 22:51.204
Oh, no, you're not gonna get me
in no New York City.

22:51.304 --> 22:54.637
For a while there, I was worried
they were gonna send you to
New York during the tournament.

22:54.741 --> 22:57.869
- Listen.
- Hey, without my good luck charm,
I'd be sunk.

22:57.978 --> 23:00.538
- [ Laughs ]
- Listen, Roone, I have
to tell you something.

23:00.647 --> 23:03.480
Oh, wait, wait.
Shh, shh, shh, shh.
I got a surprise for ya.

23:03.583 --> 23:06.450
[ Sighs ] Oh, goodness.

23:06.553 --> 23:09.716
- What is this?
- It's a real golf ball,
miniaturized down.

23:09.823 --> 23:12.917
<i>I saw it in Big Putts magazine.
And if I win this tournament...</i>

23:13.026 --> 23:15.620
I'm gonna replace it
with a real diamond.

23:15.729 --> 23:19.324
- Well, um--
- Marry me, baby.

23:19.432 --> 23:23.027
Roone, um--

23:23.136 --> 23:25.297
Oh, God.

23:27.107 --> 23:29.439
[ Horn Honking ]

23:29.543 --> 23:31.841
[ Dog Barking ]

23:31.945 --> 23:33.845
[ Rose Ratliff]
He just doesn't understand me.

23:33.947 --> 23:36.040
[ Sadie Ratliff]
So what happened?
What'd you say?

23:36.149 --> 23:38.140
I told him
I'd let him know.

23:38.251 --> 23:41.152
- You didn't tell him you were
gonna miss his tournament?
- No, I did not.

23:41.254 --> 23:43.984
It's bad enough
breaking his heart without
throwin' his game off.

23:44.090 --> 23:45.990
- Mornin', Mayor.
- Mornin', ladies.

23:46.092 --> 23:49.152
Oh, come on, Duke.
Get your tail out of that
truck, you big ol' baby!

23:49.262 --> 23:52.823
Oh, here, let me help you.
Oh! Feels like you packed
your whole damn closet.

23:52.933 --> 23:57.302
- How long you plannin'
to stay for, anyway?
- For as long as I can.

23:57.437 --> 24:01.032
- What do you mean by that?
- I mean I'm not comin' back.

24:01.174 --> 24:04.041
Are you crazy?
Does Hilda know?
Does Winona?

24:04.144 --> 24:07.443
No, and don't you tell 'em,
either, or I'll tell Roone
you're missin' his tournament.

24:07.547 --> 24:10.277
Oh, you a heart the size
of an unsoaked pinto bean.

24:10.383 --> 24:13.045
I oughta fit right in
in New York.

24:13.153 --> 24:16.281
- Mama and Papa would've
been so proud of you.
- Oh!

24:16.389 --> 24:19.119
Don't carry all your money
in one place.

24:19.226 --> 24:22.127
- Don't go into the subways.
- Don't talk to any strangers.

24:22.229 --> 24:24.288
- No. No.
- Or eat clams.

24:24.397 --> 24:27.093
Auntie Sadie, will you
bring me back a surprise?

24:27.200 --> 24:31.364
Oh, li'l Levon.
You know I wouldn't forget you.

24:31.504 --> 24:34.439
[ Sobbing ]

24:34.541 --> 24:37.203
[ Sighs ]

24:37.310 --> 24:39.210
Ooh!

24:39.312 --> 24:42.941
Now, what's that all about?
We're gonna see you in two days.

24:43.049 --> 24:46.143
- Come on, let's go.
Bye, everyone.
- Okay, you go, you go.

24:46.253 --> 24:48.244
<i>- Get in the truck.
-[ Winona ] Bye-bye!</i>

24:48.355 --> 24:50.880
- Good luck!
- Bye!

24:50.991 --> 24:54.392
Take care! Hurry home!

24:54.494 --> 24:57.054
Yee-ha!

24:57.163 --> 25:01.657
<i>.</i>

25:01.768 --> 25:05.499
<i>. [ Sadie Yodelling ]</i>

25:26.693 --> 25:30.595
<i>[ Man ] Well, first of all,
I thought I'd show you
this year's annual report.</i>

25:30.697 --> 25:32.858
<i>The photo of you two is great.</i>

25:32.966 --> 25:35.457
Oh, my God!
How did I get so fat?

25:35.568 --> 25:38.230
I look like
a walleyed salmon!

25:38.371 --> 25:41.067
What did he use,
a wide-angle lens?

25:41.207 --> 25:44.005
<i>No, he didn't.
See, I look thin.</i>

25:44.110 --> 25:48.171
<i>I-I mean I look thin.
I mean, I was sitting
near the window.</i>

25:48.281 --> 25:50.476
- There was a lot of light.
- I know what you mean.

25:50.583 --> 25:54.542
I don't understand how it is
that you can stuff your face
and nothing happens...

25:54.654 --> 25:56.815
and I subsist
on 60 calories a day...

25:56.923 --> 25:59.153
or else blow up
like a Macy's Day float.

25:59.259 --> 26:01.090
Do you mind?
Oh! Oh!

26:01.194 --> 26:03.185
Now we're not going
to Greenwich tonight.

26:03.296 --> 26:05.264
The stockholders'
meeting is at the Plaza.

26:05.365 --> 26:08.698
Get us our usual suite.
By the way, Rose...

26:08.802 --> 26:11.737
<i>Fabio Alberici
is flying in today.</i>

26:11.838 --> 26:16.138
Uh, Sadie, you know,
I know that I'm not that good
at figures, but, um--

26:16.242 --> 26:19.643
I mean, if we can't make a profit,
what makes him think he can?

26:19.746 --> 26:22.579
That's his problem.
[ Cracks Knuckles ]

26:22.649 --> 26:26.983
This deal is not closed yet,
so I think we should trot on out
to the airport and greet him.

26:27.087 --> 26:29.920
Italians love meaningless
gestures of respect.

26:30.023 --> 26:32.924
Makes them feel...
[ Cracks Knuckles ] virile.

26:33.026 --> 26:35.119
<i>- [ Laughing ]
- What are you laughing at?</i>

26:35.228 --> 26:37.526
<i>- Oh, this is another crank letter.
- From whom?</i>

26:37.630 --> 26:40.827
This R. Ratliff person
from Jupiter Hollow.

26:40.934 --> 26:44.165
<i>I've written him all sorts of
soothing letters, but he insists
on coming up with his sister...</i>

26:44.304 --> 26:48.707
to, uh, "raise some hell
and kick some snooty New York
ass at the stockholders--"

26:48.842 --> 26:51.242
Why didn't you show me this?

26:51.344 --> 26:53.312
What if he actually shows up?

26:53.446 --> 26:56.779
I mean, this is just
the kind of hysterical
intrusion I don't want.

26:56.883 --> 26:58.817
A couple of moist-eyed
bumpkins...

26:58.918 --> 27:00.852
making an impassioned
plea to save their--

27:00.954 --> 27:03.718
<i>- Well, the board is
suspicious enough as it is.
-Suspicious...</i>

27:03.823 --> 27:05.723
of what?

27:05.825 --> 27:10.524
Nothing.
I have a job for you.

27:10.630 --> 27:14.031
<i>A Harvard MBA for this?
How are we supposed to find
these Ratliff people?</i>

27:14.134 --> 27:17.103
Who do I look like to you?
Nancy Drew? I mean, really!

27:17.203 --> 27:19.569
Now, listen. These Ratliffs
are absolute hicks.

27:19.706 --> 27:23.608
<i>- There should be no problem
in finding them at all.
- Taxi!</i>

27:23.743 --> 27:26.769
- Over here, taxi!
- Chuck? Chuck!

27:26.880 --> 27:28.939
[ Horn Honking ]

27:29.082 --> 27:31.209
- Where did you go?
- I'm in the cab.

27:31.317 --> 27:33.285
[ Sadie Shelton ]
Harlan, stay to the right.

27:33.386 --> 27:36.514
[ Harlan ] Who're you kiddin'?
I haven't got lost since the day
the two of you were born.

27:36.623 --> 27:40.787
- And that was at least--
- We know how many years ago
that was, Harlan. Just drive.

27:40.894 --> 27:44.057
Where do we find
the suitcases, Rose?

27:44.164 --> 27:47.895
- Oh, here. Look.
Over here, Sadie. Over--
- Okay. All right.

27:48.001 --> 27:50.663
Oh, look at my glove.

27:50.804 --> 27:53.671
- Oh, my God.
- Here, stick with me.
Come on, now, stick with me.

27:53.773 --> 27:56.708
<i>- You're going the wrong way.
- What's the holdup here?
I'm late for a flight.</i>

27:56.843 --> 27:59.277
- Rose! Rose!
- Stay with me.

28:02.382 --> 28:04.577
- Wait here.
- Thank you, Harlan.

28:06.519 --> 28:09.420
<i>[ P.A., Indistinct ]</i>

28:12.959 --> 28:15.553
<i>- Here you are, Mr. Alberici.
- Grazie.</i>

28:15.662 --> 28:18.995
<i>Grazie, signore. Arrivederci
e buono giornata. Grazie.</i>

28:23.903 --> 28:29.398
<i>Oh, great. He's early.
Well, who looks Italian?</i>

28:34.814 --> 28:38.079
- [ Muttering Broken Italian ]
- Huh?

28:38.184 --> 28:40.652
- I don't know you foreigners.
- [ Muttering ]

28:40.753 --> 28:44.450
[ Chattering ]

28:44.557 --> 28:48.220
- Oh, I hope we didn't miss him.
- [ Sighs ]

28:48.328 --> 28:51.058
- Bus number 7 9
to Roosevelt Parkway.
- Come on, Rose.

28:51.164 --> 28:53.598
- 1 82 to Kew Gardens.
- Oh, the heck with that, Rose.

28:53.700 --> 28:56.032
I'm in New York.
I wanna act like a New Yorker.

28:56.136 --> 28:58.730
<i>-Sadie, hold on! Hold on, now.
- [ Whistles ]</i>

28:58.872 --> 29:00.806
- Hold on!
- [ Horn Honking ]

29:00.907 --> 29:03.034
- He al--
- Oh, my God!

29:03.176 --> 29:05.576
- I don't know
what I'm gonna do--
- Rose and Sadie?

29:05.678 --> 29:08.442
<i>-[ Horn Honking ]
- At last we meet.</i>

29:08.548 --> 29:10.607
Do we know you?

29:10.717 --> 29:14.084
Uh, I am Fabio Alberici.

29:14.187 --> 29:16.417
<i>Graham Sherbourne told me
to look for you.</i>

29:16.523 --> 29:18.684
But you are not easy to find.

29:18.791 --> 29:23.888
<i>They wouldn't let me park.
I had to keep circlin'and circlin'.</i>

29:23.997 --> 29:27.592
Did-Did you go and buy
yourselves brand-new outfits?

29:27.700 --> 29:29.827
How'd you know?

29:29.936 --> 29:32.302
Come over here a second.

29:34.507 --> 29:39.001
- Wow, what's goin' on?
- That Graham Sherbourne who wrote
us those shuck and jive letters.

29:39.145 --> 29:41.773
<i>I bet he sent this fella
over here to soft-soap us.</i>

29:41.881 --> 29:44.748
- Oh, but how'd they know
when we were comin' in?
- Are you kiddin'?

29:44.851 --> 29:48.582
Computer chips.
They got their ways.
We better be on guard.

29:48.688 --> 29:50.713
[ Clicks Teeth ]

29:54.561 --> 29:57.462
[ Gasps, Sighs ]

29:59.399 --> 30:02.129
[ Gasps ]

30:03.770 --> 30:06.170
<i>Sadie, don't you dare.</i>

30:06.272 --> 30:11.175
For once in my life,
I'm gonna be Joan Collins,
and you're not gonna stop me.

30:14.948 --> 30:18.440
Don't think we're always
gonna be this easy.

30:18.551 --> 30:21.315
Perhaps we should
discuss business later.

30:21.421 --> 30:23.321
Fine with me.

30:23.423 --> 30:25.323
Oh, I just don't understand it.

30:25.425 --> 30:28.326
I spoke to everyone
wearing an Armani suit.

30:32.165 --> 30:35.362
<i>[ Gasps ]
Oh, oh, that must be he.</i>

30:36.903 --> 30:40.066
- Oh! Oh! Oh, my!
- What the hell is Harlan doing?

30:43.142 --> 30:47.636
Gee, these press-on nails.
I guess I should've pressed
harder, huh?

30:51.618 --> 30:55.076
You want
the air conditioning on?

30:55.188 --> 30:59.750
Uh, it's not
n-necessary for me.

30:59.859 --> 31:02.089
I don't know if--

31:07.367 --> 31:11.030
<i>- Don't touch.
- I just wanted to feel it.</i>

31:11.170 --> 31:13.764
- God, you are so bossy.
- Be quiet.

31:13.906 --> 31:17.307
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

31:21.748 --> 31:24.478
Will one of you
get the damn phone?

31:24.584 --> 31:27.985
<i>[ Ringing Continues ]</i>

31:34.761 --> 31:36.160
[ Imitating Joan Collins ]
Hello?

31:36.262 --> 31:38.492
[ Man On Phone ]
Ah, glad I got you.

31:38.598 --> 31:42.830
Which would you prefer
in your room, roses or tulips?

31:44.370 --> 31:46.531
- Roses.
- Rose is me!

31:46.673 --> 31:48.573
Thank you.

31:48.675 --> 31:52.076
It was one of those surveys.

31:52.211 --> 31:54.645
[ Chuckles ]

31:54.781 --> 31:58.979
[ Sadie Shelton ]
Well, I'm utterly humiliated.
How could Harlan do this to us?

31:59.085 --> 32:01.986
Look at this. Not enough
to get two blocks.

32:02.088 --> 32:05.455
- Well, for God's sake,
don't tell him that.
- Oh, he'll understand.

32:05.558 --> 32:09.824
<i>- Driver, we're a little
short on cash, and I--
- [ Tires Screeching ]</i>

32:11.664 --> 32:15.122
- [ Wolf Whistles,
Catcalls In Spanish ]
- Hi.

32:15.234 --> 32:18.169
What is this hideous compulsion
you have to be honest?

32:18.271 --> 32:20.171
I-I don't know.
I'm so sorry.

32:20.273 --> 32:25.176
Now, we are going to walk
very casually, and yet very quickly.

32:25.278 --> 32:28.941
- [ Catcalls Continue ]
- [ Women Shrieking, Yelling ]

32:29.082 --> 32:32.176
[ Sadie Ratliff] Oh, Rose,
it's just so cosmopolitan.

32:34.287 --> 32:36.414
[ Gasps ] Isn't it excitin'?

32:36.522 --> 32:39.286
<i>[ Rose Ratliff ] Oh,yeah.
The noise, the smog, the crowds...</i>

32:39.392 --> 32:42.793
<i>the muggers, sex fiends,
white slavers, politicians--
it's a pistol.</i>

32:42.895 --> 32:46.763
<i>I got about as much use for it
as a toad has for spit curls.</i>

32:46.866 --> 32:52.304
[ Chuckles ] You Americans are--
are so funny, eh. Hmm.

32:56.642 --> 32:58.667
Oh, thank you.

33:12.058 --> 33:13.753
P.U.!

33:39.085 --> 33:43.988
[ Gasping ] What's goin' on?
What're we doin' here?

33:44.090 --> 33:47.150
I don't know, but don't
take your eye off your suitcase.

33:47.260 --> 33:48.989
Signorine?

33:57.837 --> 34:00.203
Wine and cheese.

34:00.306 --> 34:02.137
- Good morning.
- Oh!

34:02.241 --> 34:04.300
Welcome to the Plaza.

34:04.444 --> 34:06.344
Right this way.

34:25.465 --> 34:28.992
- Come on, Sadie. Quit gawkin'.
- [ Gasps ]

34:29.101 --> 34:31.228
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

34:31.370 --> 34:34.396
I hope we will be seeing
each other soon.

34:52.158 --> 34:54.058
Here we are.

34:57.697 --> 35:01.599
[ Panting ] It looks just like
the White House.

35:01.701 --> 35:03.601
<i>[ Manager Chuckles ]</i>

35:03.703 --> 35:06.763
Yeah, and I bet the CIA's
in the basement too.

35:06.906 --> 35:11.138
Look, let's level with each other.
Who's payin' for this room?

35:11.244 --> 35:13.474
The arrangements were made
through Moramax.

35:13.579 --> 35:15.740
<i>Is everything all right?</i>

35:15.882 --> 35:19.909
- No, it's not all right, because--
- Rose. Oh.

35:20.019 --> 35:22.681
[ Sighs ]
But I guess it'll do.

35:22.788 --> 35:25.757
We oughta cancel our
reservations at the "Y."

35:25.858 --> 35:28.793
[ Chuckling ]

35:33.332 --> 35:35.459
Testing, one, two, three.

35:35.568 --> 35:38.469
Look, a sink in the livin' room.

35:38.604 --> 35:41.903
That's what the French
call...a "bidet."

35:45.511 --> 35:47.445
The French must be
taller than me.

35:47.580 --> 35:52.449
It's me. Wasn't there supposed
to be a gift basket in this room?

35:52.552 --> 35:55.487
<i>- Will there be
anything else, ma'am?
- That's not ours.</i>

35:55.588 --> 36:00.321
- It's not?
- Oh, golly, no. Oh, I wish it was!

36:00.426 --> 36:02.326
Oh. [ Sighs ]

36:12.038 --> 36:13.938
Wow, what a room!

36:14.040 --> 36:16.838
What do you mean you've
given our suite to someone else?

36:16.943 --> 36:20.845
I-I don't know if we did.
The key's not here.

36:20.980 --> 36:24.143
I want to speak
to the manager.

36:29.188 --> 36:31.088
Rose, look at this!

36:31.190 --> 36:33.954
Red wine and cheeses
of the world!

36:34.060 --> 36:37.257
Oh! And look!
Real wooden hangers.

36:37.363 --> 36:40.355
<i>But they don't come off.
Huh.</i>

36:40.466 --> 36:43.867
"Here's to another great year
for you and Moramax. Graham."

36:44.003 --> 36:46.938
<i>- Who's Graham?
- Graham Sherbourne.</i>

36:47.073 --> 36:49.769
He's the pinstriped trouser
snake sent us those letters...

36:49.909 --> 36:53.037
and that big car and this room
and now this basket of goodies.

36:53.145 --> 36:57.013
He's just tryin' to buy us off.
Well, we are not impressed.

36:57.116 --> 36:59.016
<i>-[ Sadie Screams ]
- Whoa!</i>

36:59.118 --> 37:02.645
<i>Oh, they got the cutest little
soaps in the shape of swans.</i>

37:02.755 --> 37:04.950
Could you die?

37:05.057 --> 37:07.890
I want our room,
and I want it now!

37:07.994 --> 37:09.894
[ Tapping Keyboard ]

37:09.996 --> 37:12.487
Yes, ma'am, I can give you
the suite right next door.

37:12.598 --> 37:15.499
It's identical. I'll have the bellboy
take up your luggage.

37:15.601 --> 37:18.570
What luggage?
It's evaporated!

37:18.704 --> 37:22.504
No. There it is.
[ Panting ]

37:22.608 --> 37:25.042
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

37:27.513 --> 37:31.176
[ Both Sighing, Groaning ]

37:34.387 --> 37:37.447
I feel like my stay here
is already ruined.

37:37.556 --> 37:39.649
Oh. Enjoy your stay.

37:39.759 --> 37:42.990
I just know we're gonna have
the most marvelous time.

37:45.564 --> 37:47.691
Ooh!

37:49.535 --> 37:51.435
Lunch.

37:51.570 --> 37:54.801
Thank you. That was
the Hollowmade factory.

37:54.940 --> 37:57.534
All I could find out is
that they've already left.

37:57.677 --> 38:00.441
My God!
They may already be here.

38:00.546 --> 38:03.845
I mean, what are we gonna do?
Call every hotel in New York?

38:03.949 --> 38:08.409
I wish to God I'd never
heard of Neptune Gulch,
wherever the hell it is.

38:10.189 --> 38:12.248
Hi, everybody.
Chick Hearn here...

38:12.358 --> 38:15.327
with ESPN's coverage of
the 26th annual Mini-Masters.

38:15.428 --> 38:17.862
Oh, it's a gorgeous day
for professional putt-putt...

38:17.963 --> 38:20.864
<i>and we've got ourselves
a real barn burner.</i>

38:20.966 --> 38:23.696
<i>Let's look at the leader board.
In the first round, our leader
is Roone Dimmick...</i>

38:23.803 --> 38:26.397
<i>who's heading for the 1 2th hole
with a two-shot lead...</i>

38:26.539 --> 38:28.439
<i>six under par.</i>

38:28.541 --> 38:31.237
<i>Now let's go to the 1 2th hole
and meet another member...</i>

38:31.343 --> 38:33.811
<i>of our ESPN broadcast crew,
Ian Churchill.</i>

38:33.946 --> 38:35.345
<i>Ian.</i>

38:35.448 --> 38:37.439
<i>[ Ian Churchill ] Mr. Dimmick here
is being most thoughtful...</i>

38:37.550 --> 38:39.609
<i>at club selection
on his par-three tester.</i>

38:39.719 --> 38:42.279
<i>The Windmill, or perhaps
the Hole of Lamentation to him...</i>

38:42.388 --> 38:45.789
<i>has plagued Mr. Dimmick throughout
his otherwise stellar career.</i>

38:45.891 --> 38:48.155
<i>He's now finished
studying the lie...</i>

38:48.260 --> 38:51.957
<i>and positions himself
as a hush falls over the crowd.</i>

38:52.064 --> 38:56.262
<i>Roone! Hi there, Roone!
We're rootin'for ya!</i>

38:56.368 --> 39:00.998
Hi, Winona!
Hey, where's Rose?

39:01.140 --> 39:05.008
Well, personally, I think
she should've told you herself.

39:05.111 --> 39:07.011
Told me what?

39:07.113 --> 39:11.573
Well, this morning, she and Sadie
just up and went to New York.

39:13.919 --> 39:17.821
<i>- [ Chick Hearn ] Ladies
and gentlemen,just a second.
- Roone, what're you doin'?</i>

39:17.923 --> 39:21.188
<i>- It looks like Roone Dimmick
is walking off the course.
- Roone, where are you going?</i>

39:25.664 --> 39:27.928
[ Sadie Ratliff]
Lordy, it's high!

39:28.033 --> 39:31.025
Well, Rose, I'm going
to get my legs waxed.

39:31.170 --> 39:34.071
Are you coming?
Or are you just going
to hole up here...

39:34.173 --> 39:37.631
and pretend you're wafting
through a field of poppies?

39:37.777 --> 39:41.304
You go ahead.
I'm going to the library.
I have some reading to do.

39:41.413 --> 39:43.938
<i>Sadie. About that factory.</i>

39:44.049 --> 39:49.009
Rose, if you can't trust your
own sister, who can you trust?

39:49.121 --> 39:51.555
[ Sighs ] Darling girl.

39:51.657 --> 39:54.023
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

39:54.126 --> 39:56.856
Oh, Rose, it is
so gorgeous up here!

39:56.962 --> 40:00.489
Whoo, it makes me dizzy.
Well, I am gonna go find
that Mr. Sherbourne.

40:00.599 --> 40:04.865
- [ Bones Cracking ]
- I am gonna dip him in flour and
let him fry in his own grease.

40:05.004 --> 40:08.440
- Are you comin'?
- No, I think I'll just go for
a walk, if that's okay with you.

40:08.574 --> 40:10.474
Well, here.
Wait a minute.

40:10.576 --> 40:13.170
Don't go off without
a "Save Jupiter Hollow" button.

40:13.279 --> 40:15.338
All right, Rose.
If you insist.

40:32.464 --> 40:34.728
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

40:37.436 --> 40:39.597
<i>Hold the door.</i>

40:39.738 --> 40:42.571
<i>Hold the door!
Hold the door!</i>

40:42.675 --> 40:44.575
Moron.

40:44.677 --> 40:46.668
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

40:48.581 --> 40:51.675
- Oh!
- Oh, excuse me.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

40:51.784 --> 40:54.344
- Is everything satisfactory now?
- Oh, my, yes!

40:54.453 --> 40:58.651
That is some room! Have you
seen the view from up there?

40:58.724 --> 41:03.024
- No. I've never been
above the third floor.
- You haven't?

41:03.128 --> 41:05.596
Well, you just gotta
come up there and see it.

41:05.698 --> 41:08.360
- That's very nice of you.
- Oh, no.

41:08.467 --> 41:11.868
It would be such a shame
not to share it.

41:12.004 --> 41:15.405
And I bet it's just
so beautiful at night.

41:15.507 --> 41:18.670
Well...bye.

41:18.777 --> 41:20.870
I'll see you later.

41:20.980 --> 41:24.143
<i>-[ Phone Ringing ]
- [ Snorts ]</i>

41:24.250 --> 41:26.616
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

41:26.719 --> 41:29.688
<i>Oh, well, buongiorno.</i>

41:29.788 --> 41:33.121
[ Clears Throat ] Would you care
to join me for a drink?

41:34.927 --> 41:37.088
That's not really my style.

41:37.196 --> 41:41.098
You know, you are not
making this very easy for me.

41:41.200 --> 41:44.101
Is there any reason on Earth
why I should?

41:44.203 --> 41:47.229
I guess this is going to be
a difficult negotiation.

41:47.373 --> 41:52.310
I cannot imagine what you think
we're negotiating for.

41:52.444 --> 41:56.278
[ Laughs ]
I thought it was understood.

41:56.382 --> 42:00.113
<i>-[ Elevator Bell Dings ]
- Oh, really?</i>

42:02.288 --> 42:04.483
Eurotrash.

42:15.401 --> 42:19.701
Oh. Oh, I thought I'd just go
for a walk, if that's okay.

42:19.838 --> 42:23.239
You, walk? Ha!

42:23.375 --> 42:26.037
Well, this I gotta see.

42:28.447 --> 42:30.938
<i>[ Siren Wailing ]</i>

42:31.050 --> 42:33.450
[ Snickers ]

42:35.487 --> 42:38.854
- [ Tapping Counter]
- Oh. Hello. [ Chuckles ]

42:38.958 --> 42:42.223
Can you tell me what room
Fabio Alberici is in?

42:42.328 --> 42:44.353
Yes, he's in room...1 402?

42:44.463 --> 42:47.330
But if you're looking for him,
he's right over there.

42:49.435 --> 42:52.495
Oh, my God.
He must think I'm insane.

42:54.640 --> 42:56.540
By the way...

42:56.642 --> 43:01.011
I thought the delay when we
first checked in was inexcusable.

43:04.383 --> 43:07.011
[ Chuckles ]

43:07.119 --> 43:09.178
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

43:09.288 --> 43:11.654
<i>[ Dog Barking ]</i>

43:15.194 --> 43:17.958
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]

43:18.063 --> 43:20.224
[ Gasps ]
Oh, what cute dogs!

43:20.332 --> 43:22.232
Oh, hello.

43:26.305 --> 43:29.297
- Oh, no you don't.
- Well, it makes no difference to me.

43:29.441 --> 43:32.376
I'm getting paid
whether you ride or not.

43:32.511 --> 43:34.479
Suit yourself.

43:38.851 --> 43:41.786
What the hell are they doin'?
Are they crazy?

43:41.887 --> 43:44.583
I should've quit
this damn job years ago.

43:44.690 --> 43:47.352
<i>[ Horn Honking ]</i>

43:47.459 --> 43:50.223
Oh, Harlan!
Harlan! Harlan!

43:50.329 --> 43:52.957
Harlan! [ Gasps ]

43:53.065 --> 43:56.228
That happened to me once.

43:58.504 --> 44:01.268
<i>[ Quiet Chattering ]</i>

44:08.981 --> 44:12.417
<i>- Well, buongiorno.
- Buongiorno.</i>

44:12.518 --> 44:16.750
- You have changed your mind.
- Oh, I feel absolutely ridiculous.

44:16.855 --> 44:19.449
Of course, I should've
known who you were.

44:19.558 --> 44:21.526
You must meet a lot of people.

44:21.627 --> 44:25.085
There was such a mix-up
at the airport. I still
don't know what happened.

44:25.197 --> 44:27.358
<i>It's already forgotten.
[ Chuckles ]</i>

44:27.466 --> 44:30.094
Campari and soda.

44:30.202 --> 44:33.171
Well, hmm, business.

44:33.305 --> 44:38.208
My geologists have given me
the plans for the strip-mining
of your Jupiter Hollow.

44:38.310 --> 44:41.541
But first tell me,
would you have any objection...

44:41.647 --> 44:45.083
to us making
our transaction in yen?

44:45.184 --> 44:49.348
Mmm, laundering
some lira, are we?

44:49.455 --> 44:52.913
Ah, the Japanese
are so discreet.

44:53.025 --> 44:56.324
Well, tell me. Who buys
and sells money for you?

44:56.428 --> 44:58.328
<i>Jack Butler.</i>

44:58.430 --> 45:00.921
Jack?
I went to Yale with Jack.

45:01.033 --> 45:04.366
Oh. I did my first
hostile takeover with Jack.

45:04.503 --> 45:06.937
No! [ Laughs ]

45:08.540 --> 45:10.599
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

45:10.742 --> 45:13.506
Hi, Rose.
How's Duke doing?

45:13.612 --> 45:15.773
Duke? My dog?
[ Panting ]

45:15.881 --> 45:19.112
Boy, when you go snoopin'
into people's lives...

45:19.218 --> 45:21.345
you don't miss a trick,
do ya?

45:21.453 --> 45:24.013
I'm sorry.

45:24.123 --> 45:26.717
I'm here to see
Graham Sherbourne.

45:26.825 --> 45:28.884
Okay. He should be
in his office.

45:28.994 --> 45:31.462
And where is that?

45:31.563 --> 45:33.861
Well, where it usually is, Rose.

45:35.367 --> 45:38.200
<i>- Oh, you're a big help.
-[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

45:39.972 --> 45:42.167
Hi, Rose.

45:42.307 --> 45:44.207
Hi.

45:44.309 --> 45:46.243
Hi, Rose.

45:46.378 --> 45:49.404
Oh, hi. Hi, everyone.

45:49.515 --> 45:51.540
Just fine.
Had a good breakfast.

45:51.650 --> 45:54.448
Oatmeal. But I guess
you know that.

45:56.155 --> 46:00.216
Got on my Tuesday panties,
but I guess you know that too.

46:00.325 --> 46:02.293
- My God, it's nearly time to go.
- There he is.

46:02.394 --> 46:05.761
Well, I know, but we have
to get over to the Plaza,
for heaven's sakes.

46:05.864 --> 46:08.924
- Oh, you're right.
- Could I see your report tomorrow?

46:09.034 --> 46:11.901
- Hi, gentlemen. Hi.
- Well, what are you doing here?

46:12.037 --> 46:15.200
We were just on our way over to
the Plaza to see you and Sadie.

46:15.340 --> 46:17.274
Is, uh, everything okay?

46:17.409 --> 46:19.809
No, everything is not okay.

46:19.912 --> 46:22.574
We have to talk,
and we have to talk now.

46:22.681 --> 46:25.514
All right.
What's the problem?

46:25.617 --> 46:30.384
What's the problem?
Have you got your brains and
your balls in your briefcase?

46:30.489 --> 46:32.889
<i>-[ Man Snickers ]
Did she say "balls"?
- [ Gasps ]</i>

46:32.991 --> 46:36.427
- Wow.
- Let's just go in here
and talk, quietly.

46:36.528 --> 46:40.624
You want some reassurances
that it will be business
as usual at Hollowmade...

46:40.732 --> 46:42.632
<i>after the sale?</i>

46:42.734 --> 46:45.669
<i>- You know we can't do that.
- Well, you sure as hell better.</i>

46:45.771 --> 46:49.070
Or I'm gonna kick up a big ruckus
at the stockholders' meetin'.

46:49.174 --> 46:51.608
And I've said my piece.
Amen.

46:51.710 --> 46:55.578
[ Stammers ]
What are you talking about?
Does Sadie know how you feel?

46:55.647 --> 46:57.877
- Of course.
- Does she agree?

46:57.983 --> 47:01.214
Is a frog's ass watertight?

47:01.320 --> 47:05.222
<i>-[ Door Closes ]
- Do you suppose it's hormonal?</i>

47:05.324 --> 47:07.224
Who cares?
We're off the hook.

47:07.326 --> 47:10.159
How about some racquetball, and
where should we go for dinner?

47:10.262 --> 47:14.062
Please, please. Let me just coast
for a few precious moments...

47:14.166 --> 47:16.760
without having to make
any decisions.

47:39.791 --> 47:43.124
[ Tires Screeching ]

47:43.228 --> 47:46.629
I wanna go down
to the South Street Seaport.
Do you go that way?

47:46.732 --> 47:49.257
Step on it, please.

48:41.320 --> 48:43.288
<i>Oh, guten Morgen.</i>

48:57.002 --> 48:59.197
[ Whistles ]

49:03.075 --> 49:06.476
- Out of the way, bitch!
- Wha--Wa--Wait!

49:10.582 --> 49:13.210
[ Sighs ]

49:13.318 --> 49:15.616
I'd like a mint julep, please.

49:49.988 --> 49:51.888
Oh, no you don't!

49:51.990 --> 49:53.890
[ Man Grunts ]

49:53.992 --> 49:55.892
[ Tires Screeching ]

50:17.416 --> 50:20.010
<i>[ Punching Sounds ]</i>

50:28.126 --> 50:30.959
- Yo, Ma!
- Wha--What the heck
did you do that for?

50:31.062 --> 50:34.156
- I just wanted
to go the distance.
- Go the distance? You--

50:34.266 --> 50:36.359
- Get over here, you!
Get over here!
- Hey! Ow!

50:36.468 --> 50:38.663
- What are you doing?
- I'm gettin' you out of harm's way.

50:38.804 --> 50:42.137
<i>- Get off.
- Relax, squirt. I've tied hogs
slipperier than you.</i>

50:42.240 --> 50:44.299
- I'm not a hog. [ Grunting ]
- Oh!

50:44.443 --> 50:48.243
- Boy, you are hell on wheels!
- Well, what do you expect?

50:48.346 --> 50:52.612
- Are you responsible for this?
- His mother spoils him rotten.

50:52.717 --> 50:57.620
[ Sighs ] Well, she's a damn fool.
He's a disaster area.

50:57.722 --> 51:00.953
<i>- You don't really mean that?
- Oh,yes I do.</i>

51:01.059 --> 51:04.358
I'm very sorry. But you know,
it's never too late.

51:05.964 --> 51:08.262
Now, if you'll both excuse me...

51:08.366 --> 51:12.132
I must be getting back
to the...Plaza Hotel.

51:12.270 --> 51:14.795
<i>[Jason Muttering ]
Come back? Where you going?</i>

51:14.940 --> 51:18.239
- Wait! Your money.
- It's my money!

51:18.343 --> 51:20.743
<i>[ Horn Honking ]</i>

51:23.148 --> 51:28.916
<i>.</i>

51:53.078 --> 51:57.276
<i>. [ Yodelling ]</i>

51:57.382 --> 52:01.716
<i>[ Continues ]</i>

52:01.820 --> 52:16.099
<i>.</i>

52:16.201 --> 52:18.101
<i>[ Sadie Ratliff ]
Ya-hoo!</i>

52:22.274 --> 52:25.175
That's Sadie Shelton.

52:25.277 --> 52:28.041
<i>-[ Phone Ringing ]
- How about an ice cream soda?</i>

52:28.146 --> 52:31.081
I'd rather have
the MP-60 rocket water gun.

52:31.182 --> 52:33.707
- How about an ice cream soda?
- Messages?

52:33.818 --> 52:36.946
<i>[ Sadie Shelton Chuckling ]</i>

52:37.055 --> 52:40.149
And I get to keep
the dollars overseas,
where they aren't taxable.

52:40.258 --> 52:43.250
Uh-huh. And invest them
in a villa in Italy.

52:43.361 --> 52:45.727
[ Chuckling ]

52:45.830 --> 52:48.355
But aren't Italian property values...

52:48.466 --> 52:51.264
a little... soft right now?

52:51.369 --> 52:55.897
No. Very hard.

52:56.041 --> 52:59.943
Ooh. [ Sighs ]

53:00.078 --> 53:02.808
[ Quiet Chattering ]

53:02.914 --> 53:05.849
Hold that thought.

53:05.951 --> 53:09.216
Here's to our deliverance
from repugnant tasks.

53:09.321 --> 53:12.916
- Here's to the Ratliffs,
wherever they are.
- Hmm.

53:13.024 --> 53:16.152
<i>-.[ Violin ]
- Mmm!</i>

53:16.261 --> 53:19.788
What are the two of you doing
lazing around...

53:19.898 --> 53:23.356
guzzling Dom Perignon
on my expense account?

53:23.468 --> 53:26.494
This had better mean you found
those Ratliff people.

53:26.638 --> 53:29.163
But I thought
you changed your mind.

53:29.307 --> 53:32.572
What fantasy is this?
Are we hearing voices now,
like Joan of Arc?

53:32.677 --> 53:36.738
- But, Rose said--
- No matter what bleeding heart
sentiment my sister expressed...

53:36.848 --> 53:39.817
it has nothing to do
with what Moramax wants.

53:39.918 --> 53:42.944
Now, I want those people
found tonight.

53:43.054 --> 53:46.319
- Now?
- Now.

53:52.998 --> 53:55.523
<i>[ Women Chattering ]</i>

53:55.634 --> 53:58.797
[ Clears Throat ]
This is for you from...Sly.

53:58.937 --> 54:00.837
Thank you.

54:02.140 --> 54:04.040
[ Chuckles ]

54:23.795 --> 54:25.660
[ Sighs ]

54:25.764 --> 54:28.699
You intimidate
your subordinates so well.

54:28.800 --> 54:32.236
Don't I, though?
[ Snickers ]

54:32.370 --> 54:35.305
And what other
talents do you have?

54:35.440 --> 54:39.467
Do you...dance, perhaps?

54:39.611 --> 54:42.876
Don't think this is going to affect
my judgement in the slightest.

54:42.981 --> 54:46.473
I'm planning to gouge you
on this sale.

54:46.584 --> 54:50.452
And I...to impale you.

54:50.555 --> 54:54.582
<i>[ Tango ]</i>

54:54.693 --> 54:56.593
Thank you.

54:58.596 --> 55:02.225
- Try the "Y." Hicks
always stay at the "Y."
- I just did.

55:02.333 --> 55:04.597
- And?
- They were going there,
but they cancelled.

55:04.703 --> 55:07.433
Are you ready for this?
They're here.

55:08.873 --> 55:10.932
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

55:11.076 --> 55:13.567
Where did you get it?

55:13.712 --> 55:17.546
- It's from somebody named Sly.
- It's a bribe.

55:17.649 --> 55:20.277
They want us
to keep our mouths shut.

55:20.385 --> 55:24.116
- How come?
- They've got to be
up to somethin' terrible.

55:24.222 --> 55:28.352
- Wait until the stockholders
hear about this.
- Do they have to?

55:28.460 --> 55:30.792
What do you mean?

55:30.895 --> 55:33.125
Well,just 'cause
we take a bribe...

55:33.231 --> 55:36.325
doesn't mean we have to
do what they say.

55:36.434 --> 55:41.371
Sadie Ratliff, sometimes I wonder
if we got the same blood.

55:41.473 --> 55:45.068
<i>My own sister. Damn.</i>

55:45.210 --> 55:48.611
I can't think how things
could get any worse.

55:52.383 --> 56:01.724
<i>.</i>

56:01.826 --> 56:04.727
<i> They say the neon lights
are bright.</i>

56:04.829 --> 56:07.024
<i> On Broadway.</i>

56:09.501 --> 56:14.564
<i> They say there's always magic
in the air.</i>

56:17.776 --> 56:21.473
<i>But when you're walkin'
down that street.</i>

56:21.579 --> 56:25.447
<i>And you ain't had
enough to eat.</i>

56:25.550 --> 56:29.111
<i> The glitter rubs right off.</i>

56:29.220 --> 56:31.552
<i>And you're nowhere.</i>

56:35.426 --> 56:39.590
<i> Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh
Ooh, ooh, ooh.</i>

56:41.833 --> 56:45.394
<i> They say the women
treat you fine.</i>

56:45.503 --> 56:49.234
<i>- [ Chattering ]
-. On Broadway.</i>

56:49.374 --> 56:51.865
<i>But lookin'at them.</i>

56:52.010 --> 56:56.504
<i>Just gives me the blues.</i>

56:58.683 --> 57:00.514
<i>Doo.</i>

57:00.618 --> 57:03.587
- The Plaza.
- At the Plaza?

57:03.688 --> 57:07.522
- Where's the Plaza?
- 59th and Fifth.

57:11.095 --> 57:15.088
<i> On Broadway..</i>

57:16.634 --> 57:19.535
As soon as I get my shoes on,
I'm gonna take this evidence...

57:19.671 --> 57:22.504
and put it
in the hotel safe.

57:24.776 --> 57:27.370
Fine by me.

57:27.478 --> 57:29.742
[ Phone Rings ]

57:29.848 --> 57:32.078
- Hello?
- [ Sadie On Phone ] Rose? Listen.

57:32.183 --> 57:35.414
Did you say anything to Chuck
and Graham about calling off
the Hollowmade sale?

57:35.520 --> 57:38.546
- Of course not.
- Well, they are totally inept.

57:38.656 --> 57:42.285
Look, I want you to go
downstairs and help them
find these Ratliff people.

57:42.393 --> 57:44.520
Sadie, why can't you do it?

57:44.629 --> 57:49.123
Because Fabio has turned out
to be something of a...perk.

57:49.234 --> 57:52.135
I had plans
for the evening, Sadie.

57:52.270 --> 57:56.229
I know what your plans were.
To hole up in the room and
make love to the pastry cart.

57:56.374 --> 57:59.207
Now put down that eclair
and get downstairs.

57:59.310 --> 58:01.141
Okay, Sadie.

58:10.355 --> 58:13.847
I want to put this
in the hotel safe, please.

58:13.958 --> 58:16.085
Rose Shelton, please.

58:17.528 --> 58:19.553
Thank you. Never mind.

58:19.664 --> 58:21.598
Excuse me. Rose!

58:21.699 --> 58:24.429
- Oh! Yes?
- I've been doing a lot of thinking.

58:24.535 --> 58:27.436
- We can fix this.
- What is this?

58:27.538 --> 58:30.063
- Open it.
- Oh, you're Sly.

58:30.208 --> 58:33.268
Sly--I don't know
what you're talking about.
I couldn't be more sincere.

58:33.411 --> 58:35.345
Please. Another bribe?

58:35.446 --> 58:38.006
<i>Bri--If you don't want this,
what do you want?</i>

58:38.116 --> 58:41.017
If you think you can
buy me off with this!

58:41.119 --> 58:44.020
- Look, honey--
- Don't you touch me,
and don't you call me honey...

58:44.122 --> 58:47.819
you no-good, belly-scrapin'
pile of cow plop!

58:47.926 --> 58:50.827
<i>-[ Woman ] Come along.
-[ Boy ] What's a cow plop, Mommy?</i>

58:50.929 --> 58:53.955
Obviously, you're still upset.

58:54.065 --> 58:55.965
[ Hissing ]

58:56.067 --> 58:59.002
- [ Beads Rattling ]
- You can't outsnake me.

59:02.173 --> 59:04.573
[ Chattering ]

59:06.678 --> 59:09.647
Excuse me.
I-Is this the Plaza Hotel?

59:09.781 --> 59:11.681
It's all yours.

59:16.287 --> 59:18.619
Hey.

59:18.723 --> 59:21.920
You stand here long enough,
you see yourself come out.

59:22.026 --> 59:24.392
- What?
- Yeah.

59:24.495 --> 59:26.793
There's two of everybody
in there.

59:47.418 --> 59:50.751
The ones on the top,
and one of those cocoa truffles
with the little swirl on it.

59:55.626 --> 59:57.526
And, um...

59:57.628 --> 01:00:02.088
<i>I'll take two--
no, give me three of those
pretty parfait nougats.</i>

01:00:02.200 --> 01:00:04.100
- Surprise!
- [ Yells ]

01:00:04.202 --> 01:00:09.139
- Yes?
- I know I'm the last person
you expected to see here...

01:00:09.240 --> 01:00:11.800
and maybe you don't believe this,
but you're the gal for me...

01:00:11.943 --> 01:00:15.379
and I'm the guy for you,
and we're gonna get married and
there ain't two ways about it.

01:00:15.513 --> 01:00:19.472
- Is this some kind of a joke?
- Is that all you can say?

01:00:19.584 --> 01:00:23.020
I heard you were up here,
I come up all this way,
and you think it's a joke?

01:00:23.121 --> 01:00:26.249
[ Laughs ]
You'll have to excuse me.

01:00:26.357 --> 01:00:28.257
Oh.

01:00:28.359 --> 01:00:32.887
Can you believe
he actually tried to buy me off
with a diamond ring?

01:00:32.997 --> 01:00:37.297
I think I've earned a...
a few hours' sleep.

01:00:37.402 --> 01:00:40.838
<i>- Are you comin' to bed?
-[ Sadie ] But it's only 9.:00.</i>

01:00:40.938 --> 01:00:44.704
Ooh, boy. I never thought I'd have
to wear this old thing again.

01:00:44.809 --> 01:00:48.301
<i>Oh, Sadie, that used to be
your favorite dress.</i>

01:00:48.446 --> 01:00:50.471
Yeah, well--

01:00:50.581 --> 01:00:53.709
- Where are you goin'?
- I'm goin' downstairs.

01:00:53.818 --> 01:00:58.312
I'm not gonna stick around here
like a clove on a baked ham.
I'm gonna kick up my heels.

01:00:58.423 --> 01:01:01.119
They got dinin',
they got dancin', food, beverages.

01:01:01.225 --> 01:01:03.557
Shoot, I could stay right here
in this hotel the rest of my life...

01:01:03.661 --> 01:01:06.186
and be happy
as Beulah the cow.

01:01:06.297 --> 01:01:09.266
<i>- [ Moos ]
- I thought you was gonna help me.</i>

01:01:09.367 --> 01:01:12.928
Ratliff, Ratliff. A man
and his sister from Jupiter Hollow.

01:01:13.037 --> 01:01:15.505
I'm telling you,
they're not here.

01:01:15.606 --> 01:01:18.040
They must be registered
under an assumed name.

01:01:18.142 --> 01:01:20.872
<i>-[ Rose Shelton ]
Graham? Graham.
-[ Roone ] Graham?</i>

01:01:20.978 --> 01:01:22.912
<i>- Well, who's Graham?
- Rose?</i>

01:01:23.047 --> 01:01:25.743
- Hi, I'm Roone.
- I'm Graham.

01:01:25.850 --> 01:01:29.411
- Uh, this is Chuck.
- Howdy. Uh, y'all from Moramax?

01:01:29.520 --> 01:01:32.683
- Hi. Yes, yes, we are.
- Well, I'm from Jupiter Hollow.

01:01:32.790 --> 01:01:35.350
Jupiter Hollow?
I was born in Jupiter Hollow!

01:01:35.460 --> 01:01:37.360
And you're proud of it.

01:01:37.462 --> 01:01:40.329
Uh, do you,
do you know the Ratliffs?

01:01:40.431 --> 01:01:43.093
Well, you're standin'
right in front of one of'em.

01:01:43.201 --> 01:01:46.364
Uh, would you excuse us
for one minute?

01:01:46.504 --> 01:01:48.938
Jus-Jus--Rose.

01:01:52.443 --> 01:01:54.343
I've never seen
this person in my life.

01:01:54.445 --> 01:01:56.572
He mu--He must have seen
my picture in the annual report.

01:01:56.681 --> 01:02:00.014
- He calls himself "Roone"?
- He's "R. Ratliff."

01:02:02.120 --> 01:02:06.216
He's the factory foreman
from Hollowmade. This must be
his perverse idea of having fun.

01:02:06.324 --> 01:02:08.451
Let's just humor him
until Sadie gets here.

01:02:08.559 --> 01:02:11.221
Oh, do I have to?
Mm-hmm.

01:02:11.329 --> 01:02:14.457
Uh, Roone...

01:02:14.565 --> 01:02:16.863
would you like
to join us for dinner?

01:02:16.968 --> 01:02:19.232
Well, that sounds
like a good idea.

01:02:19.337 --> 01:02:22.431
- Yeah, I could use
a tuna fish sandwich.
- [ Laughing ]

01:02:27.178 --> 01:02:28.941
<i>Hi, there.</i>

01:02:29.013 --> 01:02:31.880
- Hello.
- Gee, you're still workin'?

01:02:31.983 --> 01:02:34.975
I bet you're lookin' forward
to gettin' off tonight, huh?

01:02:35.086 --> 01:02:37.953
- I was, uh--
- I wanna have some fun tonight.

01:02:38.055 --> 01:02:41.320
It's too early to go to bed.
You got any ideas?

01:02:42.693 --> 01:02:44.593
Maybe.

01:02:44.695 --> 01:02:46.595
Maybe I'll...
see you around.

01:02:46.697 --> 01:02:49.530
Okay. I'll keep my eye
out for ya. Bye.

01:02:51.903 --> 01:02:56.306
So, you will not take back
any paper on the sale...

01:02:56.407 --> 01:02:59.274
even if I kickback a percent
of the strip-mining profits.

01:02:59.377 --> 01:03:03.871
Absolutely not.
I insist on total liquidation.

01:03:03.981 --> 01:03:07.280
Well, this evening cannot end
until we conclude our negotiation.

01:03:07.385 --> 01:03:10.320
- Perhaps in my room, hmm?
- Ooh.

01:03:10.421 --> 01:03:12.889
Let me get my messages.
I'll meet you upstairs.

01:03:12.990 --> 01:03:17.324
<i>I, I want to change into
something less...al dente.</i>

01:03:17.428 --> 01:03:19.487
- [ Speaking Italian ]
- Mmm.

01:03:23.334 --> 01:03:27.065
[ Clears Throat ]
Do you have any messages for me?

01:03:28.940 --> 01:03:33.343
One. I get off at 1 0:00,
and I'd love to see the view
from your room.

01:03:33.444 --> 01:03:36.777
Well, we certainly
can look forward to that.

01:03:36.881 --> 01:03:38.781
[ Giggles ]

01:03:49.460 --> 01:03:53.123
[ Chuckles ]
Ma'am, could you put a little
more fire under this fish?

01:03:53.231 --> 01:03:55.563
Will ya, hon? I, I think I just
heard it holler, "Help!" [ Laughs ]

01:03:55.666 --> 01:03:57.793
Hmm.

01:03:57.902 --> 01:04:00.427
- Smooth. Very smooth.
- Mm-hmm.

01:04:01.973 --> 01:04:05.875
Excuse me. [ Chuckles ]

01:04:06.010 --> 01:04:08.342
Well, what do y'all think
about Rose?

01:04:08.446 --> 01:04:12.075
She's quite a little beauty, isn't she?
Don't you be gettin' any ideas now.

01:04:12.183 --> 01:04:14.617
- [ Laughs ]
- [ Laughs ]

01:04:16.220 --> 01:04:18.654
Oh, my God.

01:04:18.756 --> 01:04:20.656
Excuse us.

01:04:20.758 --> 01:04:22.658
I know.
I know it looks horrible.

01:04:22.760 --> 01:04:25.490
But we've got the culprit right
here. He's a professional.

01:04:25.596 --> 01:04:29.896
<i>Fake name.
Totally ingenious, totally prepared.
He actually knew Rose by sight.</i>

01:04:30.001 --> 01:04:33.459
Don't you let him out of your
sight until after tomorrow's
stockholders' meeting.

01:04:33.604 --> 01:04:36.767
Is that quite clear?
[ Grunts ]

01:04:36.907 --> 01:04:39.501
[ Sighs ]

01:04:39.644 --> 01:04:43.375
What are we supposed to do,
immobilize him with a death ray?

01:04:43.481 --> 01:04:45.381
Let me think.

01:04:48.653 --> 01:04:50.780
[ Sighs ] Stop.

01:04:50.888 --> 01:04:54.847
[ Laughs ] Oh, I'm sorry. You know,
I know it seems strange...

01:04:54.959 --> 01:04:58.360
my comin' up all this way
from Jupiter Hollow like this.

01:04:58.462 --> 01:05:01.898
- But, Rose, I love you.
- [ Coughs ]

01:05:01.999 --> 01:05:05.935
Why are you doing this to me?

01:05:06.037 --> 01:05:08.301
Well, from the first moment
I heard you were in New York...

01:05:08.439 --> 01:05:10.839
all that mattered to me
was findin' you.

01:05:10.941 --> 01:05:15.310
You can't be happy here.
I mean, the traffic alone. [ Chuckles ]

01:05:15.413 --> 01:05:18.075
I just can't see you up here
in all this traffic.

01:05:18.182 --> 01:05:21.345
And the food. I mean, back home,
we'd use this stuff as bait.

01:05:21.452 --> 01:05:23.784
Look, I'm doing
just fine, really.

01:05:23.888 --> 01:05:27.085
I know. You'd do fine
whatever spot on earth
they dropped you on.

01:05:27.191 --> 01:05:30.388
It's just--[ Sighs ]
Rose, I know you.

01:05:30.494 --> 01:05:32.826
You don't belong
in New York City.

01:05:32.930 --> 01:05:35.398
It's in your eyes.
It's all over your face.

01:05:35.499 --> 01:05:38.525
You don't belong in that,
that suit.

01:05:38.636 --> 01:05:42.470
I mean, all this Moramax stuff is
just bleedin' the heart right out of ya.

01:05:42.606 --> 01:05:45.473
You know you want a whole other
kind of life than this.

01:05:45.576 --> 01:05:49.205
[ Sighs ] I-I've never told
that to a living soul.

01:05:49.347 --> 01:05:51.212
How did you know?

01:05:51.315 --> 01:05:55.411
[ Chuckles ]
Well, I know you.

01:05:55.519 --> 01:05:59.114
- [ Sobbing ]
- Tha-Tha-That's nothin' to cry about.

01:05:59.223 --> 01:06:02.715
- [ Chuckles ] Oh, here. Here.
- [ Sobbing Continues ]

01:06:02.827 --> 01:06:05.057
Oh. Oh! [ Laughing ]

01:06:09.800 --> 01:06:11.700
Thank you.

01:06:24.849 --> 01:06:28.341
[ Speaking Italian ]

01:06:28.452 --> 01:06:30.420
Well, you're in America now.
Speak American.

01:06:30.521 --> 01:06:34.981
Y-Yes, but,
you are dressed to go out.

01:06:35.092 --> 01:06:38.892
Did you want to go out again,
or back upstairs?

01:06:38.996 --> 01:06:41.988
I was going to go back upstairs.

01:06:42.099 --> 01:06:43.999
Good.

01:06:45.636 --> 01:06:48.070
- Shall we?
- No!

01:06:48.205 --> 01:06:50.105
I can make it on my own.
You go right ahead.

01:06:50.207 --> 01:06:54.166
Ah, of course.

01:06:56.213 --> 01:07:02.015
By the way, why don't you take
this, uh, reading material now?

01:07:02.119 --> 01:07:05.111
Last thing I planned
to do tonight was read.

01:07:05.222 --> 01:07:07.122
Oh.

01:07:08.859 --> 01:07:10.759
Well.

01:07:17.635 --> 01:07:20.195
- Hi.
- You.

01:07:20.304 --> 01:07:23.364
You look almost...
almost wholesome.

01:07:23.507 --> 01:07:27.375
- What are you doing here?
- I wanted to talk to you.

01:07:27.478 --> 01:07:31.039
- Talk to me about what?
- About what you said aboutJason
in F.A.O. Schwarz.

01:07:31.148 --> 01:07:36.711
I was impressed and amazed.
It reminded me of a...
of a girl I used to know.

01:07:36.821 --> 01:07:41.815
Listen. I think we should
have lunch or something.

01:07:41.926 --> 01:07:44.622
Y-You want me
to have lunch with you?

01:07:44.728 --> 01:07:46.992
Well, I mean,
Jason too, if you want.

01:07:47.097 --> 01:07:50.464
Well, 'long as you keep him
bound and gagged.

01:07:50.568 --> 01:07:52.468
[ Chuckles ]

01:07:52.570 --> 01:07:54.538
[ Chuckles ]

01:07:54.638 --> 01:07:58.938
Well, uh, we could talk more
easily if it's just the two of us.

01:08:01.378 --> 01:08:03.175
Okay.

01:08:03.280 --> 01:08:07.216
Um, what about, uh, here?
Tomorrow, 2:00.

01:08:07.318 --> 01:08:10.378
Y-Yes. Ve-Very nice.

01:08:12.990 --> 01:08:15.686
- I'll see ya.
- Mm-hmm.

01:08:18.095 --> 01:08:22.555
Mmm! Friendly men
in this town. Mmm!

01:08:22.666 --> 01:08:26.193
[ Whistling
"I'm In The Mood For Love" ]

01:08:26.303 --> 01:08:29.328
<i>[ Whistling Continues ]</i>

01:08:29.473 --> 01:08:31.372
<i>-[ Elevator Bell Dings ]
- Have a good evening now.</i>

01:08:31.475 --> 01:08:33.466
Of course.

01:08:33.611 --> 01:08:35.977
<i>. [ Whistling Continues ]</i>

01:08:37.214 --> 01:08:39.648
<i>-[ Elevator Bell Dings ]
- [ Whistling Stops ]</i>

01:08:42.386 --> 01:08:44.286
[ Whistles ]

01:08:59.470 --> 01:09:02.131
Hey, babe.

01:09:02.273 --> 01:09:06.403
I used to be allergic to angora,
but I'm okay now.

01:09:08.479 --> 01:09:10.344
Ooh.

01:09:18.956 --> 01:09:21.550
I love to see a woman
with a good appetite.

01:09:21.658 --> 01:09:24.423
- You do?
- Mmm. [ Chuckles ]

01:09:24.528 --> 01:09:26.928
[ Clears Throat ]
I feel obliged to point out to you...

01:09:27.031 --> 01:09:29.863
that this man is a con artist
of the first rank.

01:09:29.966 --> 01:09:33.232
- Maybe he isn't.
How do you know?
- I--

01:09:33.337 --> 01:09:35.828
So where are you staying,
Roone?

01:09:35.973 --> 01:09:40.205
Well, I ain't exactly stayin'
anywhere. I just got off the
bus and come lookin' for you.

01:09:40.310 --> 01:09:45.408
Well, we have a whole suite.
Why doesn't Roone stay with us?

01:09:45.515 --> 01:09:48.109
Oh, no. I couldn't crowd you guys.
[ Chuckles ]

01:09:48.218 --> 01:09:50.118
We insist.

01:09:52.323 --> 01:09:56.259
You know, this meal has not
satisfied my appetite one iota.

01:09:56.360 --> 01:10:00.160
I got such a cravin'
for some country cookin',
I'm gettin' downright homesick.

01:10:00.264 --> 01:10:03.290
[ Whispering ]
Shameless.

01:10:03.400 --> 01:10:08.633
Hell, I only been out
of Jupiter Hollow one day...

01:10:08.772 --> 01:10:10.706
but I sure do miss it.

01:10:10.808 --> 01:10:12.867
What do you miss about it?

01:10:13.010 --> 01:10:16.912
Well, uh, my porch,
for one thing.

01:10:17.047 --> 01:10:20.847
[ Chuckles ] Nothin' like rockin' on
your porch around twilight time.

01:10:20.951 --> 01:10:25.411
[ Sighs ] Yeah, your bones
go as limp as a willow tree.

01:10:25.522 --> 01:10:28.889
And the shadow from the mountain
makes its way up my steps like--

01:10:28.993 --> 01:10:31.518
well, like an old friend
comin' to visit.

01:10:31.629 --> 01:10:33.529
- Mmm.
- And the stars!

01:10:33.631 --> 01:10:36.429
I mean, that's about the only thing
crowded aboutJupiter Hollow.

01:10:36.533 --> 01:10:39.969
Right now, the sky'd be
plumb full of stars.

01:10:41.338 --> 01:10:45.206
You know. Kids playin'
in the schoolyard...

01:10:45.309 --> 01:10:48.472
- [ Chuckles ]
- doors with no locks...

01:10:48.579 --> 01:10:51.514
folks who look you straight
in the eye and smile.

01:10:51.615 --> 01:10:56.279
Yeah, people are as close as corn
there in Jupiter Hollow.

01:10:56.387 --> 01:10:59.550
You know, when Mother Nature
looks through her window...

01:10:59.657 --> 01:11:03.388
Jupiter Hollow is the view
that she loves best.

01:11:08.999 --> 01:11:12.162
The Colbyco board
has already approved the merger.

01:11:12.269 --> 01:11:14.169
[ Clears Throat ]

01:11:14.304 --> 01:11:16.864
[ Imitating Joan Collins]
Adam, have a glass of water, please.

01:11:17.007 --> 01:11:19.237
Give 'em hell, Alexis!

01:11:19.343 --> 01:11:21.971
Golly, look at her go. She is just
runnin' that whole company.

01:11:22.079 --> 01:11:25.276
Would you turn that damn thing
down? I'm tryin' to think.

01:11:25.382 --> 01:11:28.180
Oh, you have seen that episode
a thousand times.

01:11:28.285 --> 01:11:30.583
Oh, I just love it
when she fires everybody.

01:11:30.688 --> 01:11:33.350
<i>- I'm a very direct woman.
-[ Sadie Imitating Joan Collins ]
I'm a very direct woman.</i>

01:11:33.457 --> 01:11:37.587
If I do not get your approval--
and please understand...

01:11:37.695 --> 01:11:41.756
that I have controlling interest
in Denver-Carrington--

01:11:41.865 --> 01:11:44.425
I shall fire you all
on the spot...

01:11:44.535 --> 01:11:47.197
and replace you with a board
that will approve the merger.

01:11:48.906 --> 01:11:52.273
- What's this?
- Oh, somethin' that guy
from the airport gave me.

01:11:52.376 --> 01:11:56.904
- [Joan Collins Continues, Indistinct ]
- Oh, my God.

01:11:57.014 --> 01:11:59.539
<i>- What's the matter?
- Oh, my God.</i>

01:12:01.185 --> 01:12:04.245
[ Gasps ]

01:12:04.354 --> 01:12:06.254
<i>[ Knock At Door ]</i>

01:12:10.327 --> 01:12:13.763
[ Gasps ]
Um,just,just a minute.

01:12:16.300 --> 01:12:20.999
- Roone.
- How could I go to sleep without
kissin' you good night first?

01:12:24.808 --> 01:12:27.333
[ Sighs ]

01:12:27.478 --> 01:12:29.343
Good night, darlin'.

01:12:29.446 --> 01:12:33.439
[ Sighs ] No one's ever called me
"darlin"' like that before.

01:12:33.550 --> 01:12:36.246
Well, I should hope not.

01:12:37.588 --> 01:12:40.489
- [ Laughs, Gasps ]
- Look. I want you to keep this.

01:12:41.725 --> 01:12:44.023
- And, uh--
- Oh, no, no.

01:12:44.128 --> 01:12:46.096
- Please don't fuss.
- Roone, I--

01:12:46.196 --> 01:12:48.460
- I couldn't. I--[ Chuckles ]
- Uh--

01:12:48.565 --> 01:12:51.898
Well, I better go nows.

01:12:54.571 --> 01:12:56.971
Good night, sweetheart.

01:12:58.075 --> 01:13:00.839
[ Sighs ] Good night.

01:13:02.913 --> 01:13:05.814
[ Sighing ]

01:13:10.387 --> 01:13:13.845
Don't blame me. Don't blame me.
You're the one who lost him.

01:13:13.957 --> 01:13:16.482
Well, he just bolted
for the elevator.

01:13:16.593 --> 01:13:20.495
<i>- What was I supposed to do,
wrestle him to the ground?
-[ Knock At Door ]</i>

01:13:29.439 --> 01:13:31.339
[ Chuckling ] Roone.

01:13:32.509 --> 01:13:34.409
[ Whistles ]

01:13:34.511 --> 01:13:37.139
Sure is nice you boys
lettin' me bunk here.

01:13:37.247 --> 01:13:39.147
Hey, that's classical music,
isn't it?

01:13:41.418 --> 01:13:44.251
Uh, uh, yes.
Yes, it is.

01:13:44.354 --> 01:13:47.551
Yeah, I could tell.
No lyrics.

01:13:47.658 --> 01:13:49.717
[ Both Chuckle ]

01:13:49.827 --> 01:13:51.727
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>

01:13:53.597 --> 01:13:56.896
[ Speaking Italian ]

01:13:57.000 --> 01:13:58.900
Mmm.

01:14:03.240 --> 01:14:06.266
So, what do you think
of my plans?

01:14:06.410 --> 01:14:10.176
- Fabio, you fiend!
- [ Moans ]

01:14:10.280 --> 01:14:13.772
<i>[ Roone In Shower ]
.I'm in the mood for love.</i>

01:14:13.884 --> 01:14:16.284
<i>-Simply because you're near me.
- Oh, my God!</i>

01:14:16.386 --> 01:14:19.116
He is not a Ratliff.
His name is Roone Dimmick.

01:14:19.223 --> 01:14:22.852
He's traveling with $25,
no credit cards and a harmonica.

01:14:22.960 --> 01:14:25.190
<i>- Will you look at this quilt?
-.I'm in the mood for love.</i>

01:14:25.295 --> 01:14:28.458
<i>- Oh, the workmanship!
-.Simply because.</i>

01:14:29.933 --> 01:14:31.833
. You're near me .

01:14:31.935 --> 01:14:35.530
. An-- . Hey, I like your kimono.
Get that in 'Nam?

01:14:36.740 --> 01:14:40.642
- Uh, no, Fire Island.
- Huh.

01:14:41.912 --> 01:14:44.312
Well, let's all
have a drinky, shall--

01:14:45.515 --> 01:14:48.109
<i>No, I think it's time
for beddy-bye.</i>

01:14:50.921 --> 01:14:52.718
Chuck.

01:14:52.823 --> 01:14:56.281
Hmm? Good night, Roone.

01:14:59.897 --> 01:15:03.492
Don't tell me you two guys are
sleepin' in the same bed together.

01:15:04.768 --> 01:15:08.363
- Yes.
- Gee, I feel awful about that.

01:15:08.505 --> 01:15:12.601
Now if you want,
one of you can take the couch,
and I'll share the bed.

01:15:12.743 --> 01:15:17.680
Oh--Oh, that--
That's very generous of you,
but, uh, we wouldn't hear of it.

01:15:17.814 --> 01:15:21.807
- Oh, you guys are all right.
- [ Chuckling ]

01:15:29.059 --> 01:15:32.961
[ Gasps, Sighs ]

01:15:35.232 --> 01:15:39.828
[ Muttering, Gasping ]

01:15:45.242 --> 01:15:47.870
[ Whispers ] Oh, wow.

01:16:08.031 --> 01:16:10.727
<i>[ Newscaster ]
How's the traffic out there
this morning,Joanna?</i>

01:16:10.834 --> 01:16:13.928
<i>[Joanna ] Well, we're starting
out with the Long Island
Expressway bumper to bumper.</i>

01:16:14.037 --> 01:16:16.232
<i>[ Graham ] I am upset. There's only
an hour till the meeting...</i>

01:16:16.373 --> 01:16:18.500
<i>and we don't have a chance
of finding these people!</i>

01:16:18.642 --> 01:16:22.806
<i>- Keep your voice down.
- We are not going to find the Ratliffs.</i>

01:16:22.913 --> 01:16:25.177
<i>Is that all that's botherin'
you, is findin'the Ratliffs?</i>

01:16:25.282 --> 01:16:27.807
Do you know where they are?

01:16:27.918 --> 01:16:31.752
Sure. Just let me finish
my Pop-Tarts here, and I'll
take you right to 'em.

01:16:35.759 --> 01:16:39.593
- Mornin', Rose.
- Mornin', Sadie. You're late.

01:16:39.696 --> 01:16:42.893
- I already ordered.
- Oh, good. Grapefruit.

01:16:43.000 --> 01:16:45.366
Can you believe these guys?

01:16:45.469 --> 01:16:47.369
<i>First they bribe us
to keep our mouths shut...</i>

01:16:47.504 --> 01:16:49.495
<i>then they hand us
a complete copy of their plans...</i>

01:16:49.639 --> 01:16:52.574
and if that isn't bad enough, they
got the nerve to charge $1 2.50...

01:16:52.676 --> 01:16:54.940
for four tiny little pancakes.

01:16:55.045 --> 01:16:56.910
Oh, come on, Rose.
Rose, come on now.

01:16:57.014 --> 01:17:00.142
Look. You got your butter
in the shape of a goldfish, and
you got your choice of syrups.

01:17:00.250 --> 01:17:03.879
And I know how you like to mix
and match those syrups, and--
Oh, look, they got boysenberry.

01:17:04.988 --> 01:17:08.253
Oh, Sadie.
Damn, good bread.

01:17:08.358 --> 01:17:12.226
Oh! Oh, Rose! Look!

01:17:12.329 --> 01:17:15.628
All over my brand-new
polyester jacket .

01:17:15.732 --> 01:17:17.927
Quick. Do something. Well,
go on and hurry and change.

01:17:18.035 --> 01:17:20.026
Oh, I guess so. Okay.

01:17:22.873 --> 01:17:24.773
Lord, my load is heavy.

01:17:57.674 --> 01:18:00.040
Oh, good. A grapefruit.

01:18:00.143 --> 01:18:04.011
- Where did you get that?
- Milan.

01:18:04.147 --> 01:18:06.047
Well, it's awful.

01:18:06.149 --> 01:18:10.984
[ Scoffs ] Excuse me?
I'm being criticized
by a grown woman wearing a bib?

01:18:12.489 --> 01:18:14.423
We've got to make
a good impression
with the stockholders...

01:18:14.524 --> 01:18:16.651
and you look like
you're runnin' a state prison.

01:18:18.495 --> 01:18:21.828
Well, maybe
it's a trifle severe, but--

01:18:21.932 --> 01:18:25.333
Oh, all right.
I'll change before the meeting.

01:18:25.435 --> 01:18:28.370
Now...tell me more
about...Roone.

01:18:28.505 --> 01:18:33.499
What are you botherin' me
about Roone for? You know
I'm worried about the meetin'.

01:18:33.643 --> 01:18:36.771
The "meetin"'? Why are you
worried about the "meetin"'?

01:18:36.880 --> 01:18:39.508
<i>- What's got into you?
- Well, what's got into you?</i>

01:18:39.616 --> 01:18:42.915
You know the stockholders
will do what we want.

01:18:43.019 --> 01:18:46.580
<i>- Can I get you ladies anything else?
- Do not even contemplate.</i>

01:18:46.690 --> 01:18:49.659
- Boy, you're bossy.
-Just the check, please.

01:18:54.264 --> 01:18:56.164
[ Gasps ]

01:18:58.702 --> 01:19:01.569
Is that good enough for you?

01:19:01.705 --> 01:19:04.640
Yeah, but it probably costs
$50 for each little bitty polka dot.

01:19:06.009 --> 01:19:08.239
Listen. Meet me back here,
all right?

01:19:12.082 --> 01:19:13.982
- Good morning.
- Hi.

01:19:14.084 --> 01:19:18.111
I really must have that little
polka dot number in my size.

01:19:18.221 --> 01:19:20.451
- I'm a three.
- Uh--

01:19:20.557 --> 01:19:23.082
A five.
Very well, give me a nine.

01:19:25.095 --> 01:19:26.995
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

01:19:33.737 --> 01:19:36.797
- Did you forget something?
- Oh, no, I don't think so.

01:19:36.940 --> 01:19:39.465
Can you please tell me,
is my sister here?

01:19:39.609 --> 01:19:41.668
Well, she was.

01:19:41.811 --> 01:19:44.302
- She left.
- Oh.

01:19:44.414 --> 01:19:48.043
Well, then I guess
I'll just have a little bit
of something myself. May I?

01:19:50.153 --> 01:19:52.053
[ Rose Whispering ]
Oh, excuse me.

01:19:52.155 --> 01:19:55.022
[ Sighs ] Oh, I--

01:19:55.125 --> 01:19:57.719
Ah-ah. Let me guess.
Pancakes.

01:19:57.827 --> 01:19:59.920
Yes. [ Sighs ]

01:20:04.100 --> 01:20:06.000
Madam.

01:20:07.370 --> 01:20:10.066
You can give these...
to the maid.

01:20:10.207 --> 01:20:12.107
[ Chuckles ]

01:20:25.722 --> 01:20:27.656
So what do you think?

01:20:27.757 --> 01:20:33.525
Sadie...I am so upset
about this Hollowmade sale,
I don't know what to think.

01:20:33.630 --> 01:20:35.621
<i>What are you worried
about that for?</i>

01:20:35.732 --> 01:20:38.132
We're gonna march in there,
we're gonna set things right!

01:20:38.235 --> 01:20:41.671
[ Imitating Drawl ]
Set things..."right"?

01:20:41.805 --> 01:20:44.433
Right! Come on. Let's go.

01:20:44.574 --> 01:20:47.407
[ Sighs ]
I knew I could c-count on you.

01:20:47.510 --> 01:20:49.603
[ Chuckles ]

01:20:49.713 --> 01:20:51.943
[ Sighs ]

01:20:52.048 --> 01:20:56.007
Keep the change.

01:20:56.119 --> 01:20:59.247
Hell, if I know the girls,
they oughta be havin'
breakfast about now.

01:21:01.558 --> 01:21:06.757
- The girls?
- We should have been looking for
two women. We are so stupid!

01:21:07.998 --> 01:21:10.626
Rose, I have to visit
the toilet.

01:21:10.734 --> 01:21:13.862
Well, we better hurry.
The meeting. And never say
"toilet." Say "tee-tee."

01:21:13.970 --> 01:21:15.870
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

01:21:21.311 --> 01:21:24.109
[ Sighs ] Oh, look.

01:21:36.593 --> 01:21:38.527
Well, they're not in there.

01:21:41.598 --> 01:21:44.897
- I have to go tee-tee.
- What are you talking about,
go visit the toilet?

01:21:46.002 --> 01:21:48.334
Uh, hold on a second.

01:21:50.140 --> 01:21:52.040
There they go.

01:21:59.015 --> 01:22:02.382
<i>- Oh!
- Wait a minute! I'm in here!</i>

01:22:02.485 --> 01:22:04.646
Really?

01:22:04.754 --> 01:22:07.416
Yoo-hoo.

01:22:09.225 --> 01:22:13.059
What are we doing? I mean,
look at us. We are staking out
a ladies' room.

01:22:13.163 --> 01:22:15.063
Six more seconds,
and we've got them.

01:22:15.165 --> 01:22:17.531
Can you contain yourself
for six more seconds?

01:22:18.635 --> 01:22:21.035
<i>[ Toilet Flushes ]</i>

01:22:47.497 --> 01:22:49.397
[ Both Gasp ]

01:22:54.003 --> 01:22:56.767
[ Gasping ]

01:23:09.219 --> 01:23:11.414
[ Blowing Raspberries ]

01:23:13.823 --> 01:23:15.814
- [ Screams ]
- [ Screams ]

01:23:15.925 --> 01:23:18.223
<i>[ Screaming Continues ]</i>

01:23:20.196 --> 01:23:22.460
- Whoa! Whoa!
- [ Screaming ]

01:23:22.565 --> 01:23:24.931
[ Both Gasp, Scream ]

01:23:25.034 --> 01:23:27.127
- Whoa!
- [ Screams ]

01:23:28.271 --> 01:23:30.671
[ All Screaming ]

01:23:30.774 --> 01:23:32.799
- Oh, you just get out of here!
- [ Both Screaming ]

01:23:32.942 --> 01:23:35.410
[ Screaming Continues ]

01:23:37.747 --> 01:23:40.841
They're clones.
What a cheap trick.

01:23:40.950 --> 01:23:44.283
It's pod people!
I saw that movie!

01:23:44.387 --> 01:23:47.481
- I was at the premier.
- Get back. Get back!

01:23:47.590 --> 01:23:50.821
[ Gasping ] There is no such thing
as pod people, is there?

01:23:50.927 --> 01:23:53.122
You're not my sister!

01:23:53.229 --> 01:23:55.424
- And you're not my sister.
- Thank God!

01:23:55.532 --> 01:23:58.296
- Don't touch me!
Don't touch me, I say!
- [ All Gasping, Whimpering ]

01:23:58.401 --> 01:24:01.700
- Ghastly! Ghastly!
- Are they real?

01:24:01.838 --> 01:24:03.829
They're robots. They wanna
kill us a-a-and take our places.

01:24:03.973 --> 01:24:06.237
<i>- Oh, you've seen too many movies.
- You get back.</i>

01:24:06.342 --> 01:24:10.574
- You just get back.
- We must be in some kind
of parallel universe.

01:24:10.680 --> 01:24:14.446
- That is the dumbest
damn thing I've ever heard.
- Oh, you're such a hick!

01:24:14.551 --> 01:24:17.111
- There's U.F.O. written
all over this thing!
- They're probably relatives.

01:24:17.220 --> 01:24:21.020
Relatives? How can they be?
Listen to them. They're imbeciles.

01:24:21.124 --> 01:24:23.615
- Now listen.
- Now listen. I think
what we ought to do--

01:24:23.726 --> 01:24:25.694
[ All Talking At Once ]

01:24:25.795 --> 01:24:28.286
Be quiet. We're going to go
clockwise, starting with me.

01:24:28.398 --> 01:24:32.835
- Well, how come you?
- My God, it's me
with a bad haircut.

01:24:32.936 --> 01:24:35.564
[ Gasps ] Bad?

01:24:35.705 --> 01:24:40.039
- I paid 1 2 bucks for this.
- I am going to kick your ass.

01:24:40.143 --> 01:24:42.771
- I like it.
I think if we could all--
- Stop it!

01:24:42.879 --> 01:24:47.714
All right. Who are you, and where
the hell do you come from?

01:24:47.817 --> 01:24:50.786
<i>[ Rose Ratliff ]
Rosie, Rosie. My sister Rosie.</i>

01:24:50.887 --> 01:24:53.117
- We gotta figure out
who's who here.
- Rosie.

01:24:53.223 --> 01:24:57.091
- I hope I'm still me.
- [ Sadie Ratliff] Rose,
there's a chance I could be her.

01:24:57.193 --> 01:24:59.627
- [ Gasps ] Hardly.
- Oh, isn't she divine?

01:24:59.729 --> 01:25:02.323
I know for a fact.
I'm not me. Boo-hoo.

01:25:02.432 --> 01:25:05.333
I just gotta be me.
Rosie, wait for me.

01:25:05.435 --> 01:25:07.335
[ Chattering, Indistinct ]

01:25:07.437 --> 01:25:09.371
Whoa!

01:25:11.474 --> 01:25:13.374
- How many?
- Six brothers.
- And four sisters.

01:25:13.476 --> 01:25:17.071
- And four sisters.
- Sadie, ten. You make eleven!

01:25:17.180 --> 01:25:19.080
- You sure do.
- Oh, I can't believe it.

01:25:19.182 --> 01:25:23.016
- Good morning. Good...morning.
- [ Both ] Morning.

01:25:23.119 --> 01:25:25.019
- [ Sighs ]
- [ Chuckling ]

01:25:25.121 --> 01:25:28.147
Hold it. I know who it was.
It was that rickety old Nanny Lewis.

01:25:28.258 --> 01:25:31.193
She couldn't see worth a darn.
She spent her last days puttin'
diapers on chairs.

01:25:31.294 --> 01:25:35.355
All my life I felt
like I was out of place,
like I didn't belong.

01:25:35.465 --> 01:25:39.231
<i>And I didn't.
I hate my job.</i>

01:25:39.335 --> 01:25:44.534
I hate shopping.
I hate New York in June.
How about you?

01:25:44.674 --> 01:25:47.142
I hate grits.

01:25:47.277 --> 01:25:50.644
And I hate men who smell
like beer and bean dip.

01:25:50.780 --> 01:25:54.511
And I hate makin' love in the
back of recreational vehicles!

01:25:54.617 --> 01:25:56.517
Am I rich now?

01:25:56.619 --> 01:25:59.554
<i>- We're all rich.
-[ Rose Ratliff ] Oh, to hell
with that.</i>

01:25:59.656 --> 01:26:02.216
We got a meetin' to get to.

01:26:02.325 --> 01:26:05.624
We're all on the same side,
now that we're sisters.

01:26:05.728 --> 01:26:07.787
- Right.
- Right?

01:26:07.897 --> 01:26:10.195
<i>-[ Elevator Bell Dings ]
- Of course.</i>

01:26:10.300 --> 01:26:12.200
[ Sighs ]

01:26:15.538 --> 01:26:18.598
<i>[ Sadie Shelton ]
The meeting's already started.
Now, we can't all of us go in...</i>

01:26:18.741 --> 01:26:21.369
because the spectacle of all
of this seems to upset people.

01:26:21.511 --> 01:26:25.140
So, Rose,
you take them sight-seeing.
I'll go in, call off the sale...

01:26:25.248 --> 01:26:27.148
and then we'll all go
to Elaine's for lunch.

